intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Hi. Sorry about the whole invasion thing... As you can see I have stabbed Austria, seeing as he wasn't helping me much anyway! ~N~ Obviously as things stand you are missing bits of your homeland to both me and to Austria. I just want you to know that I would like to offer again (genuinely this time) the hand of friendship. You would make a much more practical ally for me because you will soon be able to strike against the main threat in this game, France. I know me and France are on the same number of supply centres, but at the moment he has Italy as an ally and only tiny fragments of Germany and England resisting him - I currently have no allies and Russia, Austria and Italy all out to get me! ~N~ So I'm hoping I can do a deal with you to balance things up again. ~N~ So my proposal is: this turn, Moscow support Sev > Ukr, and next turn my Ukr will support Liv > War, and Moscow can move into Sev. Austria won't expect us to ally (particularly if you pretend to ally with him!), and by the next build you will have all your home Sc's back. ~N~ Basically I need your help (Italy is my back-up plan but he's allied with France), otherwise I'm out of this game. And if we work together - either one of us could win. I hope by giving up Sev as a gesture of good faith I can convince you that I mean business. ~N~ Thanks for listening!
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I was going to propose you something like that. try to have Austria moving away with GAL so its one less support to take in consideration. ~N~ Also propose him to attack me or something, so you're sure to take UKR.
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: I'm not sure he'll believe anything I say any more! And he might disband Gal or Ukr in any event. But if they're both still there you might suggest he attacks Rumania with Gal and supports you into Sevastopol with Ukr (I'm sure you can sell it!). You probably won't get Warsaw back this turn with 2 but if you get me into Ukraine to support you, we should get Warsaw back to you before the build. You can choose whether to risk taking it with 2 and take Sevastopol or to make certain of Warsaw with 3 and trust me to let you have Sevastopol next time round - I certainly wouldn't mind having the extra unit for an extra turn!
3 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Well it seems Turkey has decided to turn on me, if you want help re-taking Sevastopol then i am happy to assist. ~N~ 03:15 PM mhmm, I can support you in SEV and you give me back WAR?
4 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: This is what we exchanged. But I stick with you.
5 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: A wise choice. I can afford to let you have Sevastopol a lot more than Austria can afford to give up Warsaw!

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Looking eastward, it looks like Russia and Turkey played a phoney war just long enough to make it difficult to get everyone to oppose their juggernaut. It was well done actually & might give them the game.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, I can't trust you enough to leave ruhr as a dmz. Since you clearly will take what you can when you have sufficient force. Too bad. Why not have burgandy as a dmz? If you want to screw me over bel, you can, but don't pretend it was anything having to do with an alliance anyting else. I can't trust you. that's too bad. You let England off the hook and you cost yourself an ally. When you got bel was still up inthe air. [1179252] to build another fleet. Such is dip lirfe. Good luck to you though.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I'm sorry that you feel that way. No it certainly wasn't according to any alliance as we hadn't been behaving like allies until that point. I'm very trusting of my allies and generally leave my borders open to them. What I was seeing from you though set my radar off. Again it was a move because of maybe.

Still though, you admit that your intention was to build another fleet. That is pretty much an admission that you intended to keep Belgium for long enough to keep youself from losing that additional fleet. As it stand though, the new fleet is blue and I'm willing to work with you on how it's to be deployed.

I'm not really bantering over the morality of the issue. If we were being truly moral the Belgians would rule Belgium and the Dutch, [1413210], Portuge', and [215948] would be autonomous too. Certainly, I was able to take Belgium and I did. A point that I was up front with you about. When the roles were reversed you did the same. Belgium originally belonged to the Belgians did it not? If anything, you've seen that I will be honest about my intentions even in a situation in which it would be easier to lie.
3 FRANCE -> GERMANY: You should really be looking at Warsaw and Moscow. I'm sure that you're as surprised as I am that at least one of those builds wasn't a fleet on the North Coast of St. Pete.

I think our problem is that our playing styles are very similar and we're both used to other people seeing that our ideas have merit and going along with them. Hence we're butting heads when we'd be better served by turning our attention elsewhere.

If you are willing to set a plan that shows equal growth for both of our nations then I'm your guy. If you insist on a junior partner, then it's going to be a frustrating game for both of us.

That being said, We are in great position to split England. I get Liverpool and you get London and Edinburg. I get control of the seas though. No more than the two German fleets already in existence. What do you say? It beats Russia getting Edinburgh, and it leaves us both at seven. We'd then be able to mount an assault on Russia. Me from the north and you from the midlands.
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, there's nothing I can do except accept what's real. So, I agree with your offer. We split Eng 2-1 and even out. No benefit to fighting and lots to working together. What do you want to do?

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> ENGLAND: You have a very interesting position. As long as France stays on your side, it's quite tenable. However, if France should turn on you, you will crumble very quickly, and France is almost at the point where he doesn't need you any more. Disbanding gas tells me that you're going to focus on your northern front. Is there anything I can do to help you?

The Russians keep telling me that if I don't change sides in the south, you're going to win the game in a few years. I myself don't find this argument terribly persuasive, and in any case, I'd rather have a powerful, honest, England than a powerful, dishonest, Russia.

Do you talk much to Turkey? I find his builds encouraging; do you think our little three-way deal will continue to work out?
1 ENGLAND -> AUSTRIA: What you can do to help me is to keep the pressure on Russia! Russia is talking me up to get the spotlight off of himself. Turkey is relatively quiet, but what he does say you can take to the bank. I'm optimistic our three-way will hold up, but cautiously so, once you start to take something for granted in this game it will certainly bite you in the ass.
2 AUSTRIA -> ENGLAND: Yeah Russia is offering me the world in an oyster if I turn on Turkey. I'm sure he's offering you something similar. He's about as trustworthy as Italy, and deserves the same fate.
3 ENGLAND -> AUSTRIA: Cheers to that! ;)
4 AUSTRIA -> ENGLAND: Has Germany or Turkey said anything recently?

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Well, I'm not saying that it's a rational plan by Italy, but what other hypothesis would better explain his tactics and diplomacy from last season.

My guess is that he is a bit dissatisfied settling for the 3-way draw and is looking to establish a chance to either solo or at least remove me from the game.

I think he was hoping that I would have made an aggressive move on you, leaving myself more exposed for a stab that he was trying to line up for the fall. He was acting all paranoid about you and was trying awfully hard to convince me that you would attempt to solo, how [659259] all might try to help you solo, and all that nonsense. He was even trying to persuade me to move into Finland. I imagine that he tried to persuade the opposite (that I would try to enter Finland) to you?
1 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, Italy is still telling me that his only interests with his past and future moves are to prevent you from soloing and to establish the 3-way draw. Frankly, I don't really believe that. I think his Spring moves were intended to set up for an opportunistic stab, should he elect to follow through this fall with the intent to remove me from the game for either a solo attempt or to work toward a 2-way. He &might& be thinking of backing out of that plan now, since perhaps I didn't leave myself as wide open as he expected I might, but I really can't be too sure of his intent. His forced move on Bulgaria was perhaps intended to destroy that army (if I had self-bounced in Ser), and he was perhaps hoping that I would have overextended away from Trieste leaving that home SC open to be snatched by Tyrolia and Venice.

This fall, Italy will either follow through with the stab or he won't.

Hopefully, he'll abandon the stab, backing out of Bulgaria and moving away from my Scs. That would allow the two of us to set up and hold one of several stalemate lines that would insure that we keep 17 Scs and force the 3-way draw.

However, if Italy continues with the stab, it can only be with the intent to see me out of the game through either an Italian solo or 2-way IG draw. If that is what he chooses, I would do everything I can to throw the solo to you. So, to prepare for that contingency, I would like you to take Stp and Warsaw away from me this fall, and to also attack Tyrolia from Munich. If Italy doesn't stab me, we would still be in position to ensure the stalemate. However, if Italy does stab me and tries to press for the solo, I want you to be in position to capitalize on me throwing the solo to you.

I am doing this on a matter of principle. I've done my best to explain this situation to Italy. So, if Italy is stupid enough to throw away an easy 3-way draw position for the insane ambition of attempting a solo at my expense, he needs to be punished with a German solo. Even if his moves is actually the result of some incredible manipulation on your part, possibly including the promise of giving him a 2-way draw, he still needs to be punished with seeing you solo, and intend to ensure that this game won't end in a two-way draw.

Well, I really hope that it doesn't have to come down to this contingency, but I just wanted to let you know what I am prepared to do.
2 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: i can certainly assure you that I don't believe in [1410949] draws. and i have not had any conversation with italy regarding that. my take is that he wants to try for a solo himself, or as you said, set himself up for the attempt.

I feel hesitant to try to take war from you. are you sure you want me to try to do that? i can take stp and i can hit tyrolia, but I am really not interested in being in such a position that then I become the solo threat and end up helping italy get into the atlantic in some fashion.

I have told him very clearly that if he goes to MAO, that I will do all in my power to stop him as well and will consider us at war. so hopefully we have both given him a strong enough message that he does not make such an attempt.

but suffice to say that if he does continue down this path, I'll be there to back you up 100% and will help in any way I can.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> TURKEY: So I see you've been persuaded by Austria to join him. I don't blame you; you were trapped in that corner with nowhere to go, however I wonder where he could be offering you Scs in return for your help. He is so much larger he could basically take what he wants from me.

In addition, he's stabbed you before, and is highly likely to do so again. Be under no illusion that if and when my threat is neutralised he will turn right around and gobble you up. In your position as you were last turn you were basically secure; he couldn't defeat you without another fleet bordering Smyr, which I would have easily stopped. Now you're much more vulnerable.

I'd love it if you could reconsider your decision and join our side. England, France and I are already working together as I'm sure you've deduced, and we're set to win the fight quite easily at the moment. Our alliance was formed to stop the Austria-germany alliance, and as such our current agreement is a three way draw. We would be very willing to open that to a four way on the same understanding. As for your possible SC gains, Bulgaria, Greece, Rumania and Sevastopol would be obvious locations for Turkish occupation. Let me know your thoughts.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: I was hoping to speak to you actually. Austria has betrayed me twice, and now it is my turn to betray them. I have given the illusion that we are in am alliance, but I only said that so.he would free up units from around me. Now I am much more set up to attack him if I so wish.

Make no mistake, I am fully against him. Tell me what you need me to do and I would love to end in a draw with the three of you.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: Excellent. Well obviously at the moment I need you to prove your intentions so I'll leave that to you, but might I suggest slipping Aeg into Bul and Eastern to Aeg? It guarantees you a build and will split Austria's attention nicely.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: That was my original plan.

4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Yeah, I'll definitely keep you informed, both on Italy and otherwise. I am pragmatic though. If you change your mind let me know. I could have been a great ally for you, and another opportunity for you stab me would have arisen.

I also need to apologize for the stab and, before I start explaining why I did it and what I would like to offer now, I'd like to say I'm very keen on trying to keep the alliance with you.

So, first, some explanations on why I attacked you after you being a great ally, even letting me in the BS.
1. I am very much scared of you and Italy splitting me once Austria is gone.
2. I had promised you to move out of BS, which effectively made this spring turn the perfect moment for you to attack me. Taking BUD from GAL and moving in BS behind me would have placed you in a perfect position and I already have Italy quite willing to fight me. I have three fleets after all.
3. I guess I was tempted to find a way to keep some positional advantage over you for the time-being, as the risk of going to war now seemed less scary than the risk of you going to war with me if I start looking like an easy target.
4. Once I decided to go for the stab and thinking about what will happen after, I realized there's a good chance I may be able to offer a reasonable deal to you. Plus, everyone else being convinced we're at war is not such a bad thing.
3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: So, here's what I can suggest, I'm open to other ideas also.
1. I will move RUM-BUD with SER support and BS will hold.
2. If you keep SEV at place, so that you can't build fleets there, I will continue against Italy, if you help me you can take BUD and VIE and can take TRI?

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: This is touch and go, but we can survive.

I am moving:

Smy > Syr
Con > Smy
Ank S Con > Smy

Whatever Italy does, it will bounce (I THINK) although Bla > Bul would be VERY reassuring. If he goes for the convoy, it all bounces, and if he goes for Smyrna, the supported move should bounce it. My theory is that the supported move would likewise bounce the attack on Con....but this is untested logic.

Where does Bla come in? Autumn. I may well have A Syria in Autumn. It would need to support Ank > Smy while Bla supported Con's hold.

To make any of this work, you need Sev S War > Ukr, Pru > War, which - I am assuming - is your plan. Austrian army in Ukraine is Game Over.

If you're willing to go with the above, we can ride out this year and - Germany favourable - see Austria get a nice stab in the back. Once the German armies roll in (Tyrolia is key) Aus/Ita will be streaming back from our stalemate line and we will roll them up.

I have been trying my best to get Germany onside; but your relationship with him is the key one.

By the way, you're very low profile, please could you at least say hello?

This one is not lost at all.....it's SO saveable.... come on!
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Very sorry about my low press levels, I have an uni interview tomorrow.
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Ok GOOD LUCK with that, it actually matters!

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: What are your thoughts on how we handle the Black Sea?
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I'm not feeling comfortable with you in the Black Sea, you are threatening Sevastopol and forcing me to have a couple of units around, for protection. Having our units this way is the same than bouncing the Black Sea every turn... in that case, I would feel more comfortable bouncing.

We should stick together, I believe the alliance between Germany and France is stronger than I thought. It's a matter of time for them to move their French units to the south and the German ones to the east... their most recent builds speak by their own.

My thoughts:
& Retreat your fleet from the Black Sea this turn and we will bounce in there till we agree not to do it anymore.
& We should try to take the biggest part of Austria and Italy before be too late (French-german alliance has one more unit than us right now, we need to do it quickly)
& Let be smarter than them. Those units that are not in our common borders, are units that can be used to fight our cause, and also this way we free some tension around us. They did this on their home supply centers, but the British Islands is a mess. We need to take advantage of this situation ;)
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Okay. I'm glad I heard from you because I don't know if I will be able to log on again before the end of the phase. I will take Trieste and start shuffling armies westward, and Black Sea will fall back.
3 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Nice, our alliance is in a good shape :)

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> GERMANY: Builds are done, you've been back in 3 hrs.

Come on - look at France - you have a superb chance to take down France here - Munich to Bur, Bel to Pic, and you are guaranteed Paris in the Autumn, possibly Brest and Paris too.
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: I know this. But I am already at war with ENG and RUS, potentially with you and AUS also, so attacking FRA makes not much sense to me.

I need one sure ally in the South East. If you can come up with an overall plan that you can stick to and makes you comfortable chances are I'll accept it. But it needs to include you hitting AUS. That's the only way I will consider going against FRA. Otherwise I have no incentive to stop FRA attacking you also - actually it even makes sense for me to help him attack you - then he's not going to think about turning on me.

What would you suggest as an approach for the east part of the map?
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: If you could mop up the remains of Russia and England, letting me and Austria take out Turkey for 1 year without attacking France, that would give me enough breathing space to then turn on Austria.

As you are well aware, I simply can't attack Austria now whilst Turkey is still alive - Russia doesn't matter so much, but it could be enough of a distraction for a year to allow me to finish off Turkey with Austria's help.

You and France could continue to attack England, A/I attack R/T. Once E/R/T are finished off, it comes down to 4. I will attack Austria straight away, particularly given that I can line myself up in advance - I should only need a few units of yours - maybe 2-3 to tie up enough of Austria's units to ensure his defeat whilst allowing you to tackle France.

From there, I can return and assist you by putting pressure on France in the south.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: Sorry man, I think I will remain in the area for the time-being. I don't have a clear plan, but I am not inclined to move back. I believe this pressure will have some impact.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> TURKEY: Hi!
Austria tells me that you two are in good relationship. If you sticks together you can stop France, i think. You should conquer Russia and Germany quickly, so you can reach the 3 way draw.
To tell the truth I'm a little bit afraid that you plan to stab Austria. That way you would get into a similar good position as France has now. Because of this I plan to help a little bit France. I think if you afraid more from a France solo, it is less likely that you turns against Austria.
Of course when I will see you can't stop France without me, I will turn against him, of course only then if I would still have any unit then. :)))
1 TURKEY -> ENGLAND: You believe him when he promised to support you into Holland, then? Well, you never know. It may be true. Sadly I'm in no position to offer an alternative, so you must of course do whatever may help you survive in the immediate future.

If you manage to pull it off I'll look forward to working with you :)
2 ENGLAND -> TURKEY: No-no, he asked me to support him into Hol. I will do that now. I know that it is a dangerous movement, but I think I need to make the 3 way draw closer. For this we should eliminate Russia and Germany. I hope he won't take Lon and this way I will have one more turn to make him weaker if something turns wrong.
Survival means for me nothing, I'm playing here to help reach the draw.
3 TURKEY -> ENGLAND: The question one has to ask yourself is why wouldn't he take London? Why risk a random element such as yourself when it can be so easily replaced with a French unit under complete control?

I'm not one to tell others what to do, but I have to admit that in your shoes I'd have been more tempted to ask for German support to Denmark. He's desperate enough to need you, and it puts your unit closer to a potential stalemate line position.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: So, do you think Ank will support Con to Smy, or that Ank and Black Sea will support hold at Con? If Ank supports Con to Smy, Aeg should support hold at Smy while Smy supports Bul to Con and Greece supports Serb to Bul, that will get you Con. I'm sure Arm will support hold at Sev, so if Black Sea and Ank support hold at Con, we likely won't get Con regardless, so I'll input those orders unless you suggest otherwise.
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: First of all, sorry for not getting back to you sooner. Life has been hectic as usual and I've been seriously neglecting the game.

That is an interesting set of messages. It's not too surprising to hear that from Germany, as he is a crafty player and would do what he can diplomatically to improve his chance of potential solo, or at least strengthen his position to insure his share of the draw. However, England also echoing that concern and specifically predicting that Germany would be sending that message is an interesting play. England is quite a skilled and intelligent player as well. His ability to diplomatically deflect the 3v1 situation that he was facing is quite a testament to that, and I certainly think he is aware that a strong CPA has formed. With a strong CPA, he knows he can't make it to the draw, but at the same time, he can't just come out and attack Germany and risk further galvanizing our alliance. His best play would be to create internal tension within our alliance to try to rip us apart, while working with Germany for the time being to possibly strengthen his position to be included in the draw.

I have no grand delusions of a solo in this game. It's quite clear that you, Germany, and England are far too experienced let something like that happen. I believe the best play for me and for our CPA is to work toward the 3-way draw. Getting England out of the picture may be tricky, but I think we will be able to accomplish that. I concur with your observation that we have the failsafe of establishing the corner stalemate position (provided that we eventually clean Turkey and Russia out of that area) in order to prevent any possible ambitions of an EG alliance. However, I think that Germany is also aware that any long-term partnership with England is not in his best interests, as none of us want to see our 3-way draw turn into a 4-way draw, and hopefully he doesn't have any ambitions to leverage a partnership with England to set up for a solo attempt, which I think would only make a great mess of things.

By the way, England and Germany did not mention anything to me about watching out for an Italian solo. Actually, England has been trying to pit me against Germany, telling me that he thinks that Germany may try to solo and that we need to unite to squash that threat. I imagine that England is also talking to Germany trying to pit him against you, in order to negotiate his way into the draw possibly with you cut out of the picture. England needs to expand into France to strengthen his position and working with Germany is the only way to accomplish that.

Ok, that's enough paranoia and speculation for now. I think the less paranoid interpretation of the situation strongly reinforces the notion that Germany is committed to the CPA. Before the spring moves, he was facing potential hostility from E, F and R, but he was able to diplomatically influence England into making moves that went quite well for Germany. He moved into Sweden and can take Norway this fall as well. If he follows through with that, it'll be devastating blow on England and remove any worries about England and Germany.
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Ok, as for moves: Yes, I agree that your suggestion would probably be best. It's a safe set of orders that guarantees Smy and a Turkish disband and makes a safe play on Con if Turkey does something stupid. However, it's probably most likely that Turkey will just hold Con with support from Bla and Ank.
Just to reiterate:
Gre S Ser -> Bul
Smy S Bul -> Con
Aeg S Smy

By the way, I offered Turkey support into Sev last turn and I actually issued that order. I'll offer the same thing to him again (but I won't actually give the order this time). It would be ideal for us if used Ank to cut Arm and attacked Sev with Bla, but I know it's quite a long shot.
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: All sounds perfect, great analysiss, I'm excited we are so in tune to each other's way of thinking. I too pefer to see this CPA to the end, so will try to check my paranoia. I've got along well with Germany, and even though England is trying to pull me on his side, I will just play nice long enough to get Germany and me into position to take him down. All's looking good and I've submitted those orders we discussed. Good luck with Russia and the north!
4 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Germany is saying that the other powers are telling him that you and I have been trying to undermine him diplomatically. He seems quite annoyed, but it seems that he'll may likely give us the benefit of the doubt. I'm trying to reassure him.
5 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: He sent me a major paranoid message too. My bet is England is making some guesses and pushing his buttons. I sent Germany a long message telling him I'm 100% behind the CPA, which I am, I'm just 200% behind our alliance, so if he freaks out and does something crazy then we have the option to pull in someone else, I just hope he can keep it together.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: im afraid not. im sorry i had to help england move into ruhr that turn, i really wanted his army away from berlin.
1 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: but if it looks like you are beating him i will join in. my first mission is to ger berlin and finish off italy.
2 FRANCE -> AUSTRIA: I understand you want Berlin, and by all means, take it- pooor Russia can't hold out much longer, and better you should have it than England. ~N~ ~N~ That's really the theme here. England has 9 centers, you 8, the Turks 7. I'm essentially 5 centers up for grabs here, a swing state, if you will. England takes me over, he has 14, and can take on you and Turkey without heed; even if you or Turkey has an alliance with him, the odds are still against you. Not only does England stab her allies whenever she wants to (Germany and I are proof of that, a "Western Triangle Alliance" becoming an English Empire), but if I go, England and has you enclosed and quite probably flanked. You can take Italy, but that will still leave you enclosed, and England can then just filter in his massive navy into your Med. and all the way up the Adriatic; it'd take you and Turkey staying together to put up any sort of resistance, and, again, even then it would be a long drawn out war, and could very well end in England grinding you down (you WOULD be first in the way of his hurricane of fleets, Turkey'd have a bit more shelter, you're right there.) ~N~ ~N~ That fleet in the MAO sparked a war between England and I as he violated my waters (when I left HIS EC alone.) That fleet in the Western Med is undoubtably there to help take Spain- but it won't stop there, and it won't be the only Engish ship in the area soon.... ~N~ ~N~ I want to survive right now, not win. YOU can have Marseilles and the land that would otherwise be conquered by England. All I ask is that I keep either Paris or Portugal, and that you stop England before he wipes out everyone and gets away with his treachery.
3 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: i will not let england win. well..i will try my hardest to stop him!
4 FRANCE -> AUSTRIA: Then let's attack HIM: I'll support you along the line there, to Ruhr, Belgium, Holland, Kiel- get those, and there's an instant threat on England's doorstep. That means he has to fight for it, which less pressure on you, certainly not as large of a force in the Soth for England. ~N~ ~N~ And maybe I'll survive the day. ;) ~N~ ~N~ What do you say- take Berlin and have me help you into the Rurh and beyond?

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> RUSSIA: So we still haven't been able to work together. It feels like it is now or never.

Germany's moves don't make much sense, coming after me first to attack you later. He seems to have taken that decision when he saw you were under attack in the southeast. Which is perhaps intuitive but probably not his best decision. If ever he should help you, it is now. Turkey in my opinion is becoming the superpower more than any other in this game.

So two things can be important for you:

- Making amends with Austria to fight Turkey. Even if it would imply a limited loss, it feels important for your own survival if you could succeed doing so.
- Avoiding Germany cripples you up North as you will need that position to ensure to fight Turkey. In that last respect, I could help you if you let me.

With [1470145] left until deadline, I hope to hear from you in the near future, and to discuss specific moves that can help both of us.
1 RUSSIA -> FRANCE: I cannot resist against a triple attack Germany/Turkey/Austria... I need your help asap...
2 FRANCE -> RUSSIA: Agreed, can your fleet in Nwy support Bel-nth? That way at least we can take the threat away from Nwy next turn.

Other request would be that Boh supports Ruh-mun. If possible rather in fall than in spring but that depends on where your units will be.

If I fight Germany you should be rid of him.

As for Turkey and austria, austria tells me he wants to work with you against Turkey. He will want you to yield a territory but that should not be an issue if you can take one back from Turkey , if not this year at least next year. I know austria is quite the character but hear him out. He may have a decent proposal.

Let me know well in advance please what you can do.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: FYI - I think Germany is going to try to solo, beware! I got a message from England, asking if I'd support him into MAO, and he'd support me to Por because England wants to survive. Fair enough, but then Germany sends me a message saying I should consider having England go to MAO, it could help, and even though last time we talked he said he would be okay with me going to Tyrolia, he now asks if it can wait a season or two &and& wants to make sure it's okay if he can go to Gascony, etc., etc. The Germany has the Englishman in his hip pocket, England asked me to help him because England wants to survive this game, but it's not because he's offering to help me solo (which he clearly cannot offer), it's because he has already cut a deal with Germany to help the German solo. Russia may have even cut the same deal, so beware!

PS - Germany once said something to me about being afraid of you moving into Finland, that may actually be a good options at some point, the less comfortable Germany is right now, the less likely he goes for a solo and the more likely we three-way draw.

Thoughts?
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Those are some interesting developments. Let me mull it over. Also, I can't chat much since I'm at work now, but I'll be on later tonight.
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Sounds good. Germany is saying he will draw for sure, but what else is he supposed to say? I'm watching him closely, hopefully I'm just over-reacting.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Overall, I still think we're in pretty good shape. We don't need to push Germany back to be on par with us, we only just need to ensure that he stays under 18 Scs.

Of course, to just hold your end of the line keeping what you currently have, you would need to get fleets into Gol, WMS, and Naf.

Worst-case would be if England and France did everything they could to help Germany solo, which in the near-term would be to help him put a power-3 attack on Spa for the fall. Hopefully, some diplomatic words can rectify this situation. Perhaps, ask Germany not to enter Gas if his intent is to merely draw. Also, England and France might be jaded enough to refuse to cooperate with Germany. How does that situation look as of now?
4 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: On my end of the line, I certainly hope that Russia hasn't made a deal with Germany to make things difficult, but I think I found a set of moves that'll work relatively safely regardless. Tyrolia is a key territory and I can force you in from Ven this Spring, but Boh and even War aren't critical, as we could also just fall back to the Tyr, Vie, Gal, Ukr, Mos line. As long as you hold your end, that would still leave us with 18 Scs combined.
5 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Germany said he'd send me a long response tonight, so we'll see. I'll ask Germany about Gas, I've already told him I don't want him there, so I will stand my ground and hope for the best. I can support myself to Tyrolia, so no worries there, you can use your units to do as you see fit.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> GERMANY: Yeah, sorry, I played a game with the most ruthless German I've ever come across, we had agreed to three-way draw and he &repeatedly& stabbed me as we tried to eliminate a fourth player for a three-way, then we'd talk through it and he'd stab again. So, I do have an irrational fear of Germany at this phase of a game, but no harm, no foul, right? We take down England next year and shake hands over a game well played, sound good?
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: i hope it's sufficient. at this point both Austria and I are miffed at you for a number of quite unilateral moves you've made of late. moves that we did not deserve to be subjected to.

in the end, I decided to give you the benefit of the doubt and instead of moving to gas and mar, i bounced in gas.

at this point my expectation is that you honor a dmz in MAO and not move units there until I have taken care of england and moved my units into the proscribed 'stalemate wall' position I outlined. as you can see, neither Austria or I are going for a solo... (and neither of us CAN at this point unless we count on someone being really dumb or Cding).

Ihope you can respect that, pull back from bulgaria and honor a dmz in MAO. if those things are met, indeed we'll draw this and go home as friends in the end... if not, I'll have to come to austria's aid and we might have to finish this game as adversaries rather than allies (though we can still shake hands after haha)

looking forward to finding out which path you choose.
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: I am a pretty paranoid player and tend to freak out a bit at times, but I had no idea France would die so quickly. My fears have vanished, honestly, so I'll quit playing like a spoiled brat, no worries. Austria and I are on the same page regarding Bulgaria, at least I assume, but we shall see, I have yet to hear back from him regarding my recent message to him sharing my thoughts on the situation.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: paranoid I understand, and I appreciate that you get where things are. like I said, I'm awaiting to see how your moves play out this turn.

this is a nice 3 way right now... i mean there are possibilities for 2 ways etc but really, from our mutual position its tough to imagine them playing out as of now.
4 ITALY -> GERMANY: Absolutley not, I can't imagine a two-way, a three-way will be just fine, but thanks for the thought! ;)
5 GERMANY -> ITALY: I agree with you. I'm not interested in a two way either. I don't think the situation here calls for it.

intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Time to make plans. Are you ready to roll? :-)
How do you want to play this? We really want to see Trieste and Vienna fall this turn. After that you should be able to gobble up the Italian Scs fairly quickly I hope.
From there we should divide the map in half and aim for 17/17.
But I am really hoping that you don't get wet feet and attack me. We are positioned for the most perfect jug. I promise to be a true ally and I want to make sure that we both grow equally. I am little ahead in Scs at the moment but I am also fighting on more fronts than you - and I think after this turn you will catch up quite quickly.
Let me know what you would like to do.
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Actually when I say Trieste and Vienna fall this turn - I mean this year. They can't both fall in spring.
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Hi, yes, I'm sticking with you for sure. We're so mixed up with Italy that I don't think we can even try to turn it around. One of us has to die for the other to live...

I will move BS to CON and SER will again attack TRI. You should be able to take VIE this way.

I may get ION into the AEG, which will make things a bit easier for TRI next turn.
3 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Despite encouragement from a certain south-central European power (who shall remain nameless) I would like to assure you that I will NOT be moving to Bla this turn. I am really hoping that Bla will finally become a DMZ, freeing us both up for the Western push.
I am going to put my faith in you Turkey. I think my faith will be well placed because the mutual benefit is clear. The alternative would result in a messy quagmire that will hold us both back.
So I am counting on you attacking Tri this turn. I'll take vie in Spring and you Tri in autumn. I am excited! :-)
I think our plan is quite straight forward. But let me know if there is anything you else on your mind or any other thoughts you want to share. Or if you change your plans - message me so we can figure something else out. But this does seem to be the best move this turn.
4 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: No change of plans on my side. I'm hitting Tri and moving out of the BS. You've been a very solid ally so far and I have no desire to risk it. Italy is talking to me a lot also... but it simply makes no sense to change sides.
5 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Great! Fingers crossed this all goes well.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, has that stiff drink kicked in yet?! I think I can talk Italy down from this, it makes FAR too much sense for him and me to secure our southeast stalemate position and for him to shift at France to help you out while I finish Russia off and then I can help you with Scandinavia eventually... Are you still with us?!
1 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Yes, I'm still with you. I'm going to do my best to hold strong against France and England, but it's anybody's game right now. Except Turkey's.
2 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I wouldn't give Russia much hope either, personally!

I'd be ecstatic with a three-way draw and a middle power alliance has made all the sense in the world to me since day one, so that is my goal... Hopefully Italy will see the light and realize if he leaves France unchecked that France may very well end up with 14,000 points to his name!
3 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, can you imagine Ska attacking Norway? What if Mos supported Norway to Stp while Norwegian slid into Norway? Baltic could cover Swe while Kiel covers Den, Ruh covers Kiel and Sil covers Mun... This could get you to seven centers and a build! Think about it and let me know since Mos hitting Sev would be useful as well, but the highest priority is keeping you as strong as possible, which will also result in you being able to slow down the E/F as much as possible...
4 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: I am 100% aligned with a central powers alliance; France and England are, quite obviously, my biggest threats right now, and I must handle them. I'd love to take St. Pete; I can see that it would help both of us immensely, and if there's something I've learned this game, it's that you put a dying dog out of its misery. If Moscow will support Norway to St. Pete, I will move Norway to St. Pete and NWG to Norway per your suggestion. Similarly, Silesia will move to Munich to help cover my home centers. I've thought long and hard about this, and it is a great plan. I will gladly take your support into St. Pete.

France will get, at most, one build this turn, and after Italy's moves I can see that we are in a delicate situation. In the interest of equal growth, would you consider letting Italy hold onto Trieste, Smyrna and Ankara so that he can equip his western front with enough firepower to push back France? I would consider it a long-term investment in our continued viability, and a strong strategy to contain E/F. I eagerly await your response.
5 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Great, glad you are onboard! Moscow will support you into Stp, that works for both of us as you suggest. France is a HUGE concern and I am in agreement on Italy keeping Trieste, Smy and Ank. Glad the three of us finally appear to be on the same page, I've been pushing this Central Powers alliance since day one, here's to our success!! :-)

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> RUSSIA: Dear Russia,

Apologies for my silence the past turn. I was rather busy in real life and figuring out where I would send my fleets. But there is no real explanation or justification for my silence.

Asking me for my opinion on Germany, I always find tricky. I will try to answer as honestly and openly as I can, but please keep this to yourself. Germany is in my opinion a skilful player. He has suceeded in claiming Swe, and ould probably also take Lon and Edi. In the meanwhile, he has also build 3 fleets already which can only be used particularly against you, or perhaps against me.

If Germany would keep Swe and take Edi plus Lon, he will be the superpower of the map under the present circumstances. You and I will be at 7 after this year is my expectation, but his positioning would exceed ours.

After England is gone, you or me will be Germany's new target. If we want to avoid or limit that risk, there is always the possibility of dealing with him together, but it also depends on your objectives.

I am curious to hear what you think. Let us not discuss anything with Germany about our conversations. He has raised the possibility to be sandwiched after England is gone already a couple of time and even the slightest hint is likely to become very defensive.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Kind regards,
France
1 FRANCE -> RUSSIA: Hi Russia,
Looking forward to hearing your thoughts. The deadline will be overnight for me.
France
2 RUSSIA -> FRANCE: Also for me the deadline will be in the middle of the night, I'm european.
I think that After the fall of England and Austria we must start to think about the Kaiser.
He seems loyal but he is in the middle between me and you...

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> ITALY: No problem! I do my best not to take /anything/ in diplomacy personally, but I especially don't take busy people's lives personally. Thanks for letting me know, though.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: How do you want to handle this turn? I was thinking if we can have you pop a fleet, I could rebuild it in con and get into bs without warning that way, maybe? Haven't considered it in too much depth. Plus an army build to go to arm, and should be pretty good. Or maybe something else?
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: If things were merely busy, I guess I could handle press as usual. I'd say things are unrealistically complicated - not sure where you're from, but from where I am, the way the whole covid-19 things is being handled is simply surreal, to add a bit to other ongoing issues.

By popping a fleet you mean arranging for the disbanding of one of your fleets?

This sort of thing could be great, and seeing you overtake Russia would be a major improvement to the board as a whole.

Yet, due to sleepiness, I'll again delay any serious commitment at least until tomorrow.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: If you need a pause feel free to ask for one, gold has been really good about them and I don't think any of us would mind. I know I've gone over the supposed 2 day limit in other rounds.
4 ITALY -> TURKEY: I didn't know I could possibly go past the two days... I've already asked for my two days. In any case, as we're dealing with some previously unforeseen major relationship issues, I assume my distress will be longer than any reasonable pause. Besides, despite it being difficult to force myself to actually focus around here, I find it beneficial to have at least this obligation, work and university being halted by covid.

Thanks for the tip, though!

Apart from re-asking the questions about disbanding one of our fleets, and encouraging you again to take advantage of Russia's collapse, I wonder how you see the game developing in the next few years!
5 TURKEY -> ITALY: Sorry, yesterday turned out pretty busy.

Sorry to hear about your relationship, I know it's been a tough time for a lot of partnerships lately but I'd still rather that have stayed an abstract for you.

As for the game, yes, popping a fleet I meant disbanding one of mine as you head west so that I can rebuild it next to bs. I'm not really sure where the game is headed to be honest, this hasn't been my best round but life has conspired to out it on the back burner a bit, and so combined with not having many people besides you talking a lot, I'll admit I've been giving it less focus than I'd like. I don't think that either of us will do well if we commit to fighting, though, so I'm hoping to see you head west to take advantage of England and Germany's squabble before they make peace. Germany won't be able to make meaningful progress on his own, so you should be able to cut a sweetheart deal for your fleets against England with him I'd think. Meanwhile, a concrete signal of you actually backing off and sending units against another power would enable me to do the same and turn north. I'd expect we'd be able to eventually finish off one or the other of Germany and England and probably bog down at a 3wd after that, unless you want to try and push for a 2wd which I'd be ok with trying since as I said you're the only one really talking and I've enjoyed the communication. If the tournament is going well for you, or you want to optimize our scoring, I think I'd even be ok with us getting to the end and flipping a coin or whoever has the most points from other rounds or something, and giving that person the solo.

That was a long message, sorry more rambling than I'd intended. How do you see the game developing?

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Any response to my suggestion? Can you help me take Paris to force Germany to play fair?
1 ITALY -> ENGLAND: Hey! I'm more than interested in keeping Germany under control, which is why I took so long to eliminate France, whom I intended to employ as a proxy for that. However, France tried to outguess Germany's moves three times even though each time I had handed Germany's planned moveset beforehand!!! Anyway, that proved way too ineffective.

I have a problem, though. While long term containing German growth is evidently a priority, it makes little sense/is somewhat unfeasible to attack Germany while Russia and Turkey are poised to tear Austria apart. I mean, directly attacking the only other power in condition to assist with armies is rather risky.

That can easily change, though. Turkey, at least on paper, seems open to an assault on Russia, as far as I have assessed. Perhaps, if you could push Turkey towards that, my situation would become easier and allow me to immediately join your forces against Germany. I'm on those talks as well, but we haven't so far reached any sort of agreement regarding the Med or even the division of Austria, as our little arms race can show.

An alternative would be talking to Russia, but I assume Russia wouldn't be willing to listen to you. Besides, has Russia even bothered to answer you recently? I can't get a single word as answer!
2 ENGLAND -> ITALY: I'm not saying "direct assault on Germany now", I only asked for a support into Paris for now. with an army alone, he cannot defend it, and he's certainly not in a position to attack Russia alone if we are united in France. I can only ask that you consider it, but he is now saying he'll only work with me if I keep North Sea as a DMZ, which seems far too trusting of me to do now that he's blatantly taken advantage of me to steal my build. He didn't even set his units in a way to advance his cause toward Russia with any greater speed, so the 3 armies looking at Burgandy would seem to indicate he thinks he can direct armies westward with no risk. We may have to fight to defend our French acquisitions soon regardless, I'm just trying to be ready early
3 ITALY -> ENGLAND: I get what you're saying, but to move one army against Germany without having further resources to bring in is tantamount to scratching a lion with a short stick, let alone when there are other two powerful land powers marching my way. So, any hostile action of my army will likely trigger a German reaction.

What makes this whole situation weird is Russia's unexpected unwillingness to answer press. Has Russia bothered to write you in the last month or so? It appears as if Turkey hijacked Russia's mind.

In other circumstances, we could perhaps work with Russia. That could settle the issue with Turkey, and allow Russia and I to contain Germany on land, despite your advances in the North. Or at least give me hope of not facing a full Jugg without Germany. As it stands, I must assume Russia will never be a partner, as s/he consistently fails to answer. I mean, no kidding, Russia answered with one line on June 6th. Since them, I sent messages on June 11th, [1643277]&, [1626053]&, [1406554]&, and short notes almost daily since then. (& denote a solid message, either elaborate or with a clear question)

With that in mind, either I have Turkey on my side or Germany, otherwise I can't contain their armies. And Turkey is an unlikely partner, especially if Russia has a solid position and Austria is gone to Turkey. However, Turkey has signalled some interest in shifting North. Can you help me make that a reality? If we can get any agreement that, provided something, Turkey will move on Russia, I can seriously consider fighting Germany.

Otherwise, I fail to see how I could survive the consequences. I'm more than eager to be convinced of the contrary, so feel invited to present your arguments!, even if I find it unlikely.
4 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Russia had been entirely silent to me until yesterday, so I just figured he was a scorned and bitter player, but all of a sudden he's also willing to cooperate with me to fight Germany, &as long as I move Stp away from him

These protracted games are so annoying. Germany will only cooperate with me if I keep North Sea DMZ forever, Russia will only work with me if I entirely retreat... with my units as far separated as they are, it seems like everyone is requesting I do nothing or retreat as a condition for working together, which is annoying. But if a Jugg smashes Germany, I'd be ok with that, as I still have the backdoor on Russia and the current army distribution means Germany is in more trouble than I am (so far). But I understand your point; perhaps Spain to Mar and Por to Spain(sc) means you can cover your gains while still being in my neighborhood?
5 ITALY -> ENGLAND: We'll find a way to settle everything alright, and cooperate to achieve our goals, even if we must not be as direct as we'd like.

For now (I hope to write you again before moves, more in depth), I strongly encourage you to bounce me in Mao! This will allow us to delay anything happening in the West, while keeping Germany under the illusion that I'm working against you.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: Thank you for your detailed response, I will try to be as detailed in mine.

Indeed, you have a difficult posture due to my position in the North - but this also assures me that I have the upper hand for now and can handle a two front war with RF if need be. I appreciate that you are willing to set aside your unease and work in concert. I will not let you down so easily.

on burgundy - part of it was to assure you of my intent and motivation. part of it was to counter a potential French stab that I was concerned with. regarding russia - you can lay your heart at east on that front as well. I have a some tricks up my sleeve that you will be happy with, but just like the burgundy situation, i'd rather not divulge them as it does not benefit either of us.

however, I do have some 'marching orders' for you to consider... I want you to move Sweden to Norway. this will be KEY in making sure we get what we want and will likely produce a build for you this year. so please trust me. I am sorry I can not divulge ALL my moves to you nor tell you what Russia's moves are for fear that you will change your moves. if we continue down this path of trust and I do not see you turning on me with French (or Russian) help, then in a short season as you see my moves and I see your further commitment, then I can tell you the why and how of the moves as well. I know this is a big request, but as you said yourself, if I was going to stab you for a measly gain in edi and to be stuck between russia and france, I could do that anyways right? so please trust me.

in the south, York to Lvp is critical and I expect it to get in.

I think either wal or lon to ech can work fine. but I personally think Lon to Ech is much more important right now. yes, you want to get north and I will readily cede it to you but first and foremost, I hope you take Irish. the main reason I say not to move wal is that there is a scenario under which wal may be needed to cover liverpool in the fall and if you don't have the unit in wal, it could throw my ability to help you take norway difficult.

in the end, i wont be prickly on this particular point, for now I will put in North support London to Ech, but after you have considered things further, if you still feel you MUST move wal, then I will change my support. but Swe to Nwy and York to Lvp are key.

as for my own moves in the south, suffice to say that I do not want to give you my moves for the same reasons you outlined yourself. no gain for you and if france blocks me then it would make me doubt you right? so best not to worry about it.

like I said, I have reason to believe that russia will not have the free hand in the south that he hopes to have. let me leave it at that.

I'm committed to us... in great part because I can write you a long message like this and I know you'll respond in kind - with detail and expertise. I like that and find that games with partners such as you are far more fun and enjoyable than games with partners who write a few lines and can't think in abstract terms about the 'bigger picture' or about strategy. so thanks for your diplomatic style. ;)
1 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: Thanks for the message. I'm sadly not able to reply now and likely won't be in a position to do so until tomorrow. You will hear from me as soon as I can sit down at the cpu and think things through for a minute.
2 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: no problem. we have 28 hrs
3 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: Yeah... Sorry I can't get to this now... My mental space is full of ... real life issues. I hope those will clear sufficiently enough by tomorrow morning.
4 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: So I've read your message again with a clearer mind and here's what I have to say.

You're asking an awful lot out of me! You're more or less asking me to walk blinded through a tight and twisting corridor with only sparse words coming from you to aid my progress... I'm not comfortable with this and it's not something I'll keep doing for much longer, as I'm sure you'll understand (and your message seems to indicate that you're aware of that, so I'm not too worried).

Swe will go to Nor, Yor to Liv, Lon to Channel and Wales to Irish. The last move will either bounce and cover both the Irish and Wales, or set me up to take MAO in a year or two. The first alternative is more likely...

Russia trusts you a lot, but is nonetheless plotting your demise. I'm not saying that so to gain your trust as there's really not much for me to do on that front: either you're in fact allied with me or you're not, but it's not a question of trust that will decide that for you at this point. No, it's more simply that I'm trying to help the person I consider my ally be aware of possible dangers. Russia has explicitly talked about how we share an interest in controlling your growth. He would have me move in such a way as to force you into a tough spot in the fall, more or less forced to support him into Sweden (which he is convinced you will do).

France is not trustworthy and I'm not hearing much about him from other powers. As far as I know from what he told me, his plan is still to set himself up against you and vacate my seas. Like I said, I put very little faith in his words, but I did see them as an opportunity to throw the WT out there once more. I told him that we had not yet suffered too greatly at the hands of one another and that our positions are still quite solid if we were to decide for that kind of strategy. His reply was that we needed, among other things, to break AR and see to it that Italy doesn't have much to hope from A or T.

A WT could still be tempting to me, of course, but for now I'm only committed to this. I suggest we see how the next phase turn out where France is concerned and sell the WT if it seems likely that he'll play for it. Once the WT is on track, if that should happen, you and I would need to work right away on how we would take France out of the mix...

I take great comfort in your words and find many reasons in your messages to believe that you are indeed as dedicated to EG as I am. I'd like to offer more input, but since you seem to have the situation quite under control and do not feel ready to share intel with me, there's not much I can say that wouldn't ring like futile assumptions.
5 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: Thank u for ur trust. U will not be dissapointed. I can promise that.

After this turn, france will no longer trust me and u will be in ech for sure. Russia will still think I'm with him and will get a rude surprise in the fall.

Thanks again for ur trust

There is nowhere else England can push the fleets (and now armies, which should be a direct threat to us) other than against us.

I say we take immediate action. I can sail to Mao at once, and you can significantly delay English plans by bouncing Nor-nth. Given that your two armies (Mun and Ber) can withstand whatever Russia does, you can move Kie-den, ensuring England can't sneak into Denmark, and also allowing you to build a new fleet.

Otherwise... how else do you plan to deal with England?

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> GERMANY: So, as I look at it, I expect England to support Bel-pic. This leaves us a couple of options.

Supporting you into Gas has the downside of allowing France to retreat into Paris. If you were to move another army to Burgundy, that would be no problem, but I can't see how you would do that without leaving yourself vulnerable to Russia. Do you think England would be willing to possibly support your fleet into Brest?

If we either order Bur-gas, Mars S Bur-gas and Gol-spa, or Mars S Gol-spa and Bur-gas cuts support and France sneaks into Paris, France's only unit near Brest will be the army in Paris, which your army will be able to hit and ensure Pic-bre supported by the English fleet works. If you consider appropriate, I can already message England on that, urging the English fleet to support you in, instead of the other way around.

Though in theory a setback, France will end up losing Spain and Brest, and conquering Paris, thus disbanding. You'll keep your SC count, and Paris will be easily retaken against a 2 SC France the next year. Given that Portugal will likely fall next year as well, I'll be able to afford handing you Marseilles as well, while I assume England will eventually want Brest.

What are your thoughts on this?
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: I am moving paris to protect the sc & hopefully support eng to brest. Hope this is ok - i want to be a good ally
2 ITALY -> ITALY: Ok, it seems to be all set regarding the convoy.

I had an idea, though. Do you think you can possibly persuade Russia to enter flawed orders?

I don't know how it would be best to pull that off, but our position would be even better if Serbia-rumania actually worked.
3 ITALY -> GERMANY: Well, this is ok, but it appears to be slightly ineffective. But bear in mind that you'll need to move Bel-pic for the attack on Belgium to succeed, or else the single army in Gascony can effectively defend Brest.

But, just to understand your relationship with England, you don't think England would support you into Brest if, given France sneaking into Paris, it made more sense?

0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I am thinking about playing for a three-way draw with you and France. I have not mentioned it to France yet, but I do think that he is cooperating against England. 1 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: A draw sounds like a good idea to me. I have to admit I am feeling a touch nervous about being the smallest (though most easily defended, I guess?) member of that proposed finishing group.

3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: I guess we will see. It really depends on what England does. I would guess he goes out like most people in this situation -- uncertain and divided.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Here's what I propose: Let me move Ven back to Pie. You support yourself to Ven. I have a unit to spare, so that won't hurt me. Hold off on taking London for this turn, and take it next year. In the meantime, I can work my army back to Paris, as per our exchange, and then England will be dead so I can move my fleets south while you take those centers.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: ?This makes no sense?

Ok, I guess the others talked a lot. But let's go through this one by one:
1. Why move back to PIE? You will place in MAR anyway next turn and can then go back to take PAR and BRE? This is a full retreat and you're giving them a center. I cannot support myself to VEN alone - it's 2 vs. 3 if TRI helps.

2. You don't want me to take LON, but are ok to lose another center? Come on, you can't expect me to be ok with this in any way. What is the point? I don't want to lie to you, I'm moving as I told you - GAS-BUR, BUR-MUN, NS-LON, HOL-NS with support from NOR. I am in a position where I really think I don't need to lie to you.

3. Look, my main objective for this game was to make up for missing game 1. I can achieve this with a 3-way or 2-way draw also. I know that getting a solo will have implications, it always does...

Anyway, my point is simple - I have a stalemate line against the East. They can't do anything to me, nor can they help you in any way. I don't want to fight you, as this will only lead me to a draw. However, we need to keep pushing east.

For all practical purposes if you control the Mediterranean you can always stalemate me there, so you will hold me hostage if I decide to attack you in full.

It is in your interest to take Italy, I am not joking about this. Look at the map and you will see that this will give you value and power that you do not have currently against me. If we fight now you'll die, and I have a good shot at finding other allies on similar terms, a lot of people are desperate in this situation.

I am really not ok with retreating from Italy. This will be a huge mistake and you're not doing yourself a favor. TUN and VEN are exactly the reason I am interested in working with you, otherwise I would have accepted AUS/It's offer of a 3-way draw a long time ago.

I'd strongly suggest that you stick with me on this one. Unless I'm missing something it will be plain wrong to go against me at this point. I have no problem with you planning for your 'independence', it's only normal, but let's be smart and not lose the game over it.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I'm not losing the game over it. The retreat from Ven was not a proposition to go against you. You have a glut of armies, and if you are indeed moving out, you will have enough to take Italy. I was not thinking about a build...poor calculations on my part. Like I said before, I look at this map for about 5 minutes a day. I'm far from in form here.

Obviously I lose if I fight you. I'm not thick. But you are nearly accusing me of turning against you, when all actions I have done have been in support of you. You moved into my homeland, and I supported you. You then took my home centers against my wishes, and I supported you. You then moved south which serves no purpose but to launch at attack on Spain and Mar, and now I am the one who is being called into question for raising some minor concerns about my remaining centers? At what point did that sound like me attacking you?

I have fleets all over the Med that over power all others. I have no means of opposing you on land. Please stop threatening me with ultimatums. You don't want me to move to Pie? Fine. I will take your support to Rome. You take London, I take Edi, I build in Mar, I take back my centers.

Watch. This is me trusting you again. Again. And again. If I were judging by past moves, one would assume that Mar will be gone next turn. But this is my attempt again to prove myself wrong. Let's see what happens.
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Sorry if I was too harsh. I have no issue with anything you've done so far and know you've done nothing against me the whole game. I just reacted like this because what you suggested was not optimal and it sounded like an ultimatum itself - I couldn't just agree to it.

As for you trusting me - I know I cannot expect this from you - so I'm asking you to trust me, I am trying to explain how I see things, so that we can reach a logical conclusion and move in a way that is constructive for both. Forget the trust, let's approach this more pragmatically.

I have pushed the others into the corner without any ability to react, you can go all the way to TUR and we can eliminate everyone else if they don't get organized soon. They way things are going this may very well end up as a 2-way draw.

0 GERMANY -> ITALY: thank you for the message - i will get back to you later tonight. but in short, I think you are right about France, keeping him 'on-side' for the information may be most effective.

as for Austria - I am concerned... but not enough to make any rash moves.
1 ITALY -> GERMANY: Sounds good, I look forward to your message.
2 GERMANY -> ITALY: italy. I have heard that not only have you told others of every detail of every promise I've made to you - but that you have explicitly decided NOT to help me take paris =(

I am curious why all this might be? did I not retreat from burgundy as promised to help you get a build? have I not kept Tyrolia clear? have I not pushed for austria NOT to build in triest and have I not pushed him to move on russia so our CPA can move forward? have I not stabbed england exactly when you asked me to rather than on my own timeframe?

I'm just curious why you'd go off and ensure that I would not get a build out of paris when I've done all of that. what have I NOT done or what have I done that you did not like?

can I cound on my italian ally to help me achieve a build this season or no?
3 ITALY -> GERMANY: Very odd message. Exactly what are you accusing me of, I'm confused?

As I understand it, Gas can tap Bur while Brest taps Pic and you don't get Paris, not sure how I can help with that.

I am 100% on board with a CPA. I have been pretty open with Austria, so maybe Austria is the one leaking info, I don't know sine I don't know what you are talking about. Perhaps others are making good guessing and getting you to confess things you shouldn't? I thought we were good to go. You see Gas supported me into Mar, and we have discussed me staying on France's good side, until the proper moment, is your "freak out" related to that somehow?

England is very good at twisting things and guessing what others may be saying. As I told you, England told me that you would say something about Austria, and then you did. Perhaps he's got you confessing things he was merely guessing at?

Give me a few more details and I'll give you an honest answer, but for now, I'm with you 100%, as well as with the CPA 100%. I'm confident England is trying to replace you in that three-way draw scenario, so be careful, the guy is crafty.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I can't believe how France is just giving the game to Germany.... This is just bonkers. Can I ask you to move Sev to Armenia, so we can remove Turkey, or do you think he could be useful?
1 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I must admit I've had to suspend disbelief over your moves too, so six of one....

I'd love to move into behind Turkey, and take him out, but am (understandably, I think) still a little nervous about Austria. If we can get a more complete plan, I'd be happy to do so.
2 ITALY -> RUSSIA: Austria and I are talking frantically with France to try and get him to stop assisting Germany to the win.

That, frankly, was the outcome I hadn't expected. I had expected F and G to be fighting, whilst, honestly, Austria and I eventually removed you two, leading to a joint alliance against one of the two bigger powers, leading to a 3 way draw with A/I and one of F and G.,

The stab by Germany, yet with France assisting, has left me gobsmacked - I never expected that, especially as, in league play, he gets no points for a second place to a win.

Austria and I now have no choice - we have to work with everyone left - you, me and him, to try and achieve a draw. France will, I think, work with us as he has said he will switch sides as long as he can guarantee particpating in a draw that leaves him surviving.

I think a blockade is workable here. Moscow and Sev support each other, Ukraine supports Warsaw, Gal supports Warsaw, Rum supports Gal, Vienna and Tyrolia support each other, Venice works with Rome, whilst Adriatic, Ionian, Mars, MAO, Tunis fleets can set up a blockade in the west.

Smyrna, Sev and Bul can take down the remains of Turkey, leading to an extra unit for Italy and Russia to assist in stalemate duties.

France, Austria, Russia and Italy work for a five way draw with Germany - eminently achievable, as the stalemate line is already there in most places.

I'm copying this to all parties - France, Austria and Russia (to who this message was originally written).

I seriously think this will work. Otherwise, we just limply hand the win to Germany, and concede defeat in the League season after just two games, as a win in the last two games is unlikely...

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> TURKEY: No worries, glad you found some time, and I realize I didn't respond to you either. Weekends can be hard.

For what I am concerned, I would think we just need to play our game. Work with allies, rally others against each other where we need to, but never directly attack. There are exceptions when they are on the stalemate line and required to take the solo. Otherwise, one country just needs to get to the stalemate/solo line, tap those territories first and then raise the peace-flag for that territory, which cannot be the intention.

That is pretty much what I was thinking of. What do you think?
1 TURKEY -> FRANCE: The idea has merit.

May I request access to the Tyr Sea, by the way? It would be rather useful for opening up avenues of attack.
2 FRANCE -> TURKEY: That would depend on the circumstances. Tyrs opens up the avenue to my southern provinces so I am little reluctant. I would not be opposed to support you to Nap for instance.
