intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> ITALY: Sorry, your message came in after I'd gone to sleep last night.

That's very flattering about my press, I don't know that I deserve it but I appreciate the compliment :). I'd say actually you have my vote for best press, but that being turkey hasn't been too bad; people at least talk on this board. One of my other rounds as Austria, I have seen, without exaggeration, 3 messages from Russia the whole game so far, two of which were in global and not about the game. Compared to that, having Austria threatening to throw the game is pretty palatable!

My current plans for the fleet, which is why I sent Smyrna instead of con to Aegean, is once I can control Greece and Serbia, con goes back to BS, and then I have one fleet to play defense while I build armies to push further north into Austria, with the second fleet either supporting that defense or helping against Trieste.

Of course that depends on what allowances and support I can get from you, but with Austria taking such a hard line he gets the power or he throws to Russia, at such an early stage, I don't see him as being someone that I could work with long term. I suspect if his press to me is like this, he wouldn't have been endearing himself to you either, and so I'm hoping to get your support against him in exchange for Trieste and some combination of moving the fleets further back and providing a strong front against Russia by being the one in bud to provide you a buffer. I know currently Austria provides that buffer, but hopefully you see me as a better long term option, plus the center in tri.

That's all a bit distant though - more immediately, I could support you to Greece so you can send an extra fleet to make progress against France, rather than just being a distraction while England makes progress.
1 ITALY -> TURKEY: With no intention to downplay the title I just awarded you, but at times it is rare to find coherent sentences, well divided in theme-based paragraphs and making sense overall. In rougher seas, proper capitalization and punctuation also get positive marks. Anyway, it is clear you belong to the group of players who can play and communicate with ease, and, honestly, that's a relief. I've seen these bizarre behaviours in the tournament as well! Surprising.

Indeed, I had not noticed you moved in from Smyrna, and I appreciate your explanation. Now, to business.

Austria's relations with me are quite ok, actually, except for the fact that Austria does not seem thoroughly engaged in looking for viable long-term alternatives. It is as if they failed to see how close we're to being unable to stop a Jugg. In this, I hope you're genuine about your apprehensions about Russia, whose growth in Central Europe can easily outpace everyone else, should the attack on Germany work, especially considering England's passivity.

As for my view of the Balkans, yes, I'd like Austria removed, and Trieste does please me. I would be comfortable with a division where you got the majority of the Balkans (Bulgaria, Serbia, Rumania and Budapest to start with, beyond any questioning), provided your units, especially your fleet, are deployed in a non-threatening manner.

Yet, and I ask your forgiveness beforehand, I can't immediately jump in. Firstly because I have no available resources of my own (though the advance on France seems assured, now) to tackle Austria and do my part of it, and secondly because I need some reassurance that you'll not just take the opportunity and get yourself into Ionian.

While I understand the advantages of getting your fleets past Greece, it will just force me to fight a long uphill campaign as an underdog, which I hope I'll be able to carry on thanks to possible gains in the West. Besides, it will help raise the alarm throughout the board regarding 'Turkish aggressive expansion' - everyone tends to be very compassionate towards Italy, if Italy is the last bastion of defence against Turkish fleets all the way to England.

So, in advance, I give you my word I'll respect your sphere of influence, especially as I'm concerned with Russia growing too much. I appreciate the offer of support into Greece, and assume we'd have to debate how Vienna and Greece would be handled, but that's for the future. I would be glad to assist you in Greece in one season or two (even if I suspect you don't actually need my assistance). But all that would require you not attacking Ionian.

More than simply not attacking Ionian this very season, which I expect you not to, I'd obviously ask you to redeploy your fleets in a less threatening way. I acknowledge, though, that you'd be unable to do that without showing your true colours to Russia, so this needs perfect timing.

Consequently, I suggest you use Eas to hit Ionian, while you attack Greece (Alb-gre with double support). This disbands the Austrian fleet, keeps you with five Scs, showcase your intentions of not getting past Ionian, and allows me to convoy to Albania with Austria's assent, from where we can easily support you into Serbia. If timed along Con-bla, can get you Serbia and Rumania in the same year. Anyway, I digress.

Can you commit not to actually attack Ionian? This is, to me, a necessary precondition to any cooperation.
2 TURKEY -> ITALY: Just a quick reply before bed: I can definitely commit to not actually attacking ionian, but you can't convoy to alb anymore since your army is now in NA. (you're correct if guessing I was expecting the convoy last season which is why I went to alb in the first place, when I had entered moves before I read your message last season :) )

So for this season, am I correctly interpreting that you'd like to support hold Greece and have me cut the support so you can maintain good relations with Austria a little longer, but I still get Greece, rather than taking Greece yourself and building in Venice to get tri next year?
3 ITALY -> TURKEY: As for your move to Albania, I know that feeling when you're confident to outguess your opponent and somehow things don't work as expected...

Anyway, as for the convoy I mentioned, I meant for next season (Spring). I can conceivably move the army back to Tunis now, and the convoy may be exactly what Austria is hoping for in the Spring, thereby ensuring it happen, only to get you to Serbia/me in Trieste in the Autumn. I haven't figured all that already, but it was meant for the near future.

You not attacking Ionian (ideally, never attacking Ionian) is the single most important thing in ensuring this can work, so, exactly, my idea would be for you to conquer Greece without it being clear I'm hostile to Austria. I could not risk it all by going after Austria without knowing whether or not you'll comply with 'not attacking Ionian nor deploying aggressively towards that end'.

Consequently, I naturally expect you not to conquer Greece with a fleet and follow with Con-aeg. Rather, using an army to conquer Greece would be a nice way of not deploying three fleets against me.
4 ITALY -> TURKEY: Which, more than a request to minimize your offensive power, is clearly required for your moves to be in line with the course of action, regarding the Black Sea and Russia, that you outlined before. Which is why I'd be alarmed if your actions were particularly opposed to your stated goals.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> FRANCE: I know you said you don't have a bunch of time, and may be happy to be out of this game, but thought I'd just check with you to see if you are interested in a little experiment. It's working title is Help Italy Solo, but there's another version very similar to mine that's called See If You Can Get Italy On The Verge Of A Solo And Then Screw Him Over For Spite And/Or Try To Get On A Stalemate Line For A Draw. Both titles are very good, and I'll let you decide in the end what to call it, and you can even think on it for quite some time!! :)

Anyway, My guess is that Cly and Iri will bounce in Lvp. My first request would be that you take MAO to NAO while Por moves to MAO, Spain goes to Mar and Lyo goes to Spain. SO, if you take NAO, you live on, in whatever capacity you choose, but if you don't, Por won't take MAO and you die. I think it sounds like an interesting experiment, but my opinion is pretty meaningless, so let me know what you think, it would be fun and I think we'd both learn a thing or two &and& you can call it quits at any time... Please do give it your full consideration, it should be a learning experience at the least.

PS - Please don't tell anyone anything we discuss, or if you are bitter with me and want to insure this game immediately ends in a three-way CPA, you can tell others, I don't really have much to lose, so it's your call! ;)
1 ITALY -> FRANCE: PPS - Don't get me wrong, I'm all about getting revenge... So, maybe you want to get a bit of revenge against Germany?!?! :)
2 FRANCE -> ITALY: Yeah, the name of my current plan was "make sure Germany doesn't solo". I'll consider moving to MAO
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: Hey, you are in MAO, you'd need to move to NAO! Plus, you can't win if you are dead, you can't even draw when dead. I'm sure you will get other offers to consider, the longer you live, so you could give it a go for one year, even if your only goal is to totally freak the German out, he will &lose it&, guaranteed!

Anyway, I'm a 100% revenge sort of guy, the person that I am most "bitter" with, I'll do anything/everything in my power to take them down, or at least put their demise in motion, I don't ever want anyone to ever think they can stab me and live to tell the tale, but I digress.

How about you update the order to attack NAO and sleep on it? If you don't attack NAO, you are virtually locking in a three-way and thus rewarding the German for how he's treated you in this game, which I hope you find even half as unacceptable as I do (though in a "fun", it's just part of the game, sort of thing, I'm not actually a raging lunatic, it's all in the spirit of war)!! :)

0 GERMANY -> TURKEY: Well, I tried to make it work with Italy, it made a lot more sense for me than allying with you from my position. I'm happy to give you support from Ukraine too and I'll take Moscow at a later time.
1 GERMANY -> TURKEY: Italy truly is the worst ally I have ever tried to make. He thinks that him having Sevastopol and below is a fair division of territory. You probably know if you have spoken to him. As I said, I will support Sevastopol to Rumania from Ukraine and Galicia, let me know that you are going to use it though, otherwise I'll do something else.

By the way, my changing sides should be a surprise to Italy, so I don't expect the support from Galicia to be broken. However, any bizarre moves from Italy at this point wouldn't be completely out of character.
2 TURKEY -> GERMANY: Yes, I will be moving Sevas to Rumania. I have also had several conversations with Italy where he has had unreasonable expectations as to who should get which territories. I think the quicker we can get him out of the way the better since he is such a wild card in terms of moves.
3 GERMANY -> TURKEY: I had a look at his games. It seems the ones he has won have almost all been gunboats. No surprise really.
4 TURKEY -> GERMANY: Yeah, he's not so much for the diplomacy part of this whole thing.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: I have worked things out with France to a reasonable degree so I'm hopeful he will not be helping England out in the near term. now if I do decide to keep Burgundy or take Pic, then yes, he'll probably work against me in the fall.

For the time being, my #1 fear is Baltic Sea. that is far too dangerous a spot for me to allow England into and it would truly cost me if he managed to slip there then to berlin or kiel. I have to cover it.

Also - it looks like you are making some headway in the south no? most likely you'll get black sea this spring as turkey covers ankara and smy covers con dont you think? My understanding regarding Sweden was that you had offered it to me this year. am I recollecting correctly?

Of course, if I can convoy across successfully and get edi, then that is a moot point, I will have the build I need to face off against F (and I was hoping for italian help though now that he and austria are fighting, i'm not so sure I'll get it). But if I can't get Edi this year, if I'm blocked etc, i was hoping to pick up a build from sweden.

one idea that might help us both is if you move Norway to Norwegian and Stp to Norway, that way we will have two on edi and 3 on swe (or 2 if he bounces you) and we can ensure two builds between us, in which case we can split them.

what do you think of that idea? to move nwy to nwg?
1 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Yeah, I like that idea. I am just a bit apprehensive of England moving to Finland. In which case, I'd have to cover St P with A NOR and thus be unable to help you into Sweden.

I am very happy helping you get Sweden if I see that you are committed to moving against France. Otherwise, I am apprehensive about giving you another build. I am sure you understand. So if you make an attempt to hold Burgundy (or take Picardy, I think that would be easier), I will be happy to support you into Sweden. If not, I'll have to wait and see how the situation looks in the fall.

Also, I don't think Austria and Italy are fighting. Italy asked Austria to waive his build and it looks like Austria acquiesced.

I also expect that Black Sea and Smyrna will bounce in Ankara. Turkey has might quite clear that he'll cede his centers to Austria instead of Italy and I.
2 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: really? why would turkey do that? he attacked you not the other way around - and austria stabbed him after he gave austria help. does not make too much sense to me. I'll talk to turkey and see if he can be convinced to see the danger of austria. thanks for point out the waived build, I did think something was amiss last turn but did not pay enough attention to note it. you are right. what happened with the move to gre and gre to ion then? do you know?

as for sweden, I would want my build exactly to be able to go after france. I will continue to press against france, you'll see that. so hopefully this should not be an issue.

are you going to take nwg then? that will be very important in order to figure out edi/swe - like I said, I think we can figure it out in a way that we each get one build and we would not have to pick one over the other.
3 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Yes, I am going to take Norwegian.

Austria promised Italy Greece, and Austria said that he'd move to Aegean with Eastern Med's support. I think Austria's move to Ion was just a misorder but I'm not entirely sure.

As for Turkey, I don't know why he's giving Austria his centers, but he's publicly announced it.
4 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: publicly? like to you guys in the south?

ahhh... the italy/austria situation now makes more sense. so that's why he did not build. so does this mean they are going to be allied now? where does that leave you with austria you think?

i was hoping italy would get a build and help with france, I can still hope for a move to pie, but i'm not entirely sure if it will materialize.

i think if we each get a build this season, that would make things much easier for us next year. I just hope that France does not retreat from England, that would be the worst outcome of my move to bur. =(
5 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: I dont know, its tough to read Austria. He is saying all the right things. I think you have a shot convincing Italy to go to Piedmont; the deferred build should mean he's pretty trusting of Austria.

And yes, Turkey sent all three of us identical messages saying that unless we stopped attacking him, he'd give Austria all of his centers. I assumed it was just a desperate gambit but so far it appears to have been a credible threat.

Was the Burgundy move prearranged? France says it was; but I don't understand why he would tell me that (regardless of whether he's lying or not)

0 ITALY -> GERMANY: Now that France is committed against England, have you considered switching sides? Could be an excellent powerplay that leaves you with two countries off balance rather than a really strong France secure in his corner.
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: Nah, RUS and TUR have just allied for good and you hit AUS at the same time - this is a huge risk for the whole East to collapse. I will wait for at least a year to see how things develop there before making any changes.
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: If you are worried about the juggernaught, I think you can trust that I have a handle on the situation.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: :) I don't really think you do. I wish you did, but this is not what I hear from the others. Depending on how AUS reacts you might be in a real trouble. Don't count on RUS and TUR to start fighting any time soon.

In any case, to the main point of the discussion, I really don't need a war with FRA now and think it will be a bad decision for me.
4 ITALY -> GERMANY: You see, the thing is. I didn't tell either of them that I was stabbing. So unless you have heard something from them recently, things have changed.

As for France, he is about to get a lot of growth pretty quickly. I want you to fight him because obviously that means he won't fight me. But I actually think its far more likely for him to fight you given his northern orientation.
5 GERMANY -> ITALY: But that's exactly my point - they agreed on an alliance at the same time you stabbed - how did you come to the conclusion that this is good for you? If you and AUS keep fighting you're both dead, this is what I see.

I know FRA will expand and maybe take 2 centers. I will take care to cover myself as much as possible, this is why I made an army and not a fleet.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: Sorry I didn't reply earlier; I was out for this afternoon and evening by the time you messaged me.

Serious decisions will have to wait until tomorrow, when I'm less tired, but I will address a few points.

The issue (for everyone who messaged me suddenly wanting to cooperate, at least) wasn't that you had six Scs, but that you were poised for seven.

I also think your warnings about a juggernaut are overwrought.

F Ionian S F Aegean - Eastern Med is guaranteed to succeed. Once it does, and if Austria moves F Greece- Aegean to bounce out a potential move to Aegean by F Con, then Italy can't be expelled from the Eastern Med. Once he has the Eastern Med, all they have to do is support another fleet into the Aegean, use that fleet to support Bulgaria into Con while tapping A Smyrna from Eastern Med and Turkey is down another SC. Rinse and repeat for taking Smyrna. I'm not seeing the "impenetrable" part. And that's if Russia makes no move against him. Turkey is on the ropes, and he knows it.

That's why I'm not particularly concerned about the juggernaut. It isn't as scary when it's just one Russian. I'm more worried about Italy and Austria, if they don't have a falling out.

After France moved on London, Russia and I agreed to a temporary NAP; hence why I haven't moved on Stp. As that time has passed, however, I'm open to the possibility. I will sleep on your suggestion.
1 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: alright sounds good, hope you sleep well
2 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: So your suggestion, as I understand it, is for France to push through Piedmont while you and I move all our units east, to St. Petersburg, Finland, and so forth, and take down Russia as cleanly as possible.

I doubt Russia would survive it. I'm just not sure where I'd go after St. Petersburg. Assuming you want Moscow, as most German players do, I wouldn't really have anywhere to grow. What is your plan for that point?

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: England, what are you doing?!?

You are guaranteeing that we will be picked apart by Russia/Italy/Turkey. We were in such great position, and the only way we could screw it up is by one of us stabbing the other.

Thankfully, it's nothing that can't be fixed. Please, please, please, tell me you will reverse your moves this fall. If you don't, you will have a lot of French fleets headed your way.
1 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: You are in a similar position to Turkey. Turkey has a clear opportunity to stab Russia, but he knows better than that. Because if he destabilizes Russia it only strengthens France/England/Germany.

By destabilizing Germany, you will benefit in the short term, but Russia/Italy/Turkey will benefit in the long term. Germany will be unable to hold its line, and you and I will fall next.

If you think you are going to solo, you are sorely mistaken. Because you will leave Germany and me no choice but to turn around and try to eliminate you.
2 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Cannot send message; this country has muted you.
3 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Cannot send message; this country has muted you.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, I hope you'll think on it and agree that the best thing for Austria and Turkey is the fall of Germany. England has cut a good deal with Russia at St. P, and Russia's strong at Warsaw and Moscow, meaning Austria needs to expand into Germany. If Germany and Russia stand, it wont be long before Austria and Turkey start looking at each other with hungry eyes.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: I know you might not lend me any assistance as you're still distrustful of my good intention, though of course I could hope for your support at Belgium, but if you at least see to England's move at MAO and Italy, you'll find yet that I'm a good ally to you. If not, you'll be stuck between England and Italy, both of them more experienced players, and they both need your 5 SC for a win (good luck with that!)
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I do think that you are viewing things in a much too simplisitic way. Italy is not geared to attack me, and I have no intention oif attacking her, and besides- she has so many better areas to expand. Austria or, if she IS allied with Italy, then Italy can attack you, unfortunaltely (even you admitted it), and then Turkey, if Italy and Austria want to get someone in the corner and take out a power (and I think, after the loss of Sevastopol, Russia would porbably help with that, too, unless Turkey and Russia reach an accord.) ~N~ ~N~ In any case, I am a threat to no one. England? He does have an unpredictable personality. Still, I don't watch trouble, so I'm not about to start a fight against him; let him go to the MAO- if he tries to attack me (and I hope he doesn't, I really hope the West can be settled so we can focus on the East, but if he tries, he'll find my centers covered) then I guess the Global community will have to take a look. ~N~ ~N~ To sum up my postion, if this is WWI Europe, then I'm really playing this more like I'm America than France- and that Burgundy line, that area, is my Atlantic ocean. So you can see why I needed you out- I don't want to get my hands dirty in this until I'm sure who's with me and who's not. I've spoken to everyone and, at times, everyone's seemed a friend, and at times, some have seen like enemies. One or two have remained consistent in their position; I'd like to think they're safe, and telling the truth (however much you can actually do that in this game) but most importantly- they are NOT a threat. 2 down, so that leaves four of you. And I'm getting a bout 3 stories from the 4 of you. So I'll stay here, moderate, work out deals, and play peacemaker if you want, but I'm content to wait until someone shows their colors. It's really a choice of two sides to take, and I think you know which sides those are- both say the other is going to attack me. I'm the bait- I'll see who goes first. ~N~ ~N~ If we form a coatlition, know I am, when in a serious one with no backstabbers or liars, loyal to the bitter end. ~N~ ~N~ And know that if you are my enemy, I WON'T just go away........ ~N~ ~N~ But again, I just say "you" because it's you i'm speaking to, no accusation being made. :)
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Interesting points. If there's anything I've learned playing diplomacy its that trying to remain a 'neutral' power is a sure fire way to ensure that others ally against you, and when they attack you are without allies. In WTA Diplomacy, no one survives alone, even a vastly superior power. Well, as long as you're not attacking me, I guess I'll settle for that.
4 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I said I have one or two I consider allies, I just am not helping, directly, with their military effort.
5 GERMANY -> GERMANY: NOTES
6 GERMANY -> GERMANY: France has taken Belgium, he is against me, and is onside with England I think
7 GERMANY -> GERMANY: Yes, definitely allied with England

2. I am not so close to winning. Yes, I can take out FRA and he's sided with me, but he also holds me at gun-point, as without TUN and/or Italy I can never get to 18.

3. I also feel it is right for FRA to be part of any potential draw, he's been my ally so I'd prefer to reward him rather than someone else. What you and IT suggested was that I take him out and draw with you two. I could not advance against you, so I had to get FRA to move from the South.

3 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I will think on it... I also would rather avoid a mass draw, however my ability to keep you from a solo without Italy and now Russia is unfortunately limited (though in the last league, I did hold out for a 2 way draw with you when I could have taken a solo, so perhaps you will do likewise). Additionally, just as you do not want to betray France due to his help earlier, so I do not want to betray Italy (who has been a staunch ally).

Where would you invision the final borders being?
4 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: The way things stand I have a good shot for a 2-way draw with FRA in the end. You have all deadlocked yourself and I can't see how anyone can actually make any move, in any direction.

I'm not really sure if there's much I can really offer at that stage, the simple fact is that we have a deadlock ourselves with RUS, where you are neither taking him out nor letting me take him out.

If you have a specific suggestion I'd be happy to hear it, but I see no reason to change course now. Bulk up or you'll die, this is my only advice at this stage.

Plus Austria is still being pretty belligerent and making any negotiation start with me ceding Serbia and any claim in Greece, which is an understandable stance but trying to negotiate from a position of strength doesn't endear him or seem promising for being able to hurry the hatchet.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: His& trying to negotiate from a position of strength I mean.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: Sorry about not replying the last message, I simply forgot it. Though I must say it was a well written one. In fact, your messages are consistently the best on the board. It must be somewhat hellish to be the most talkative player around and be stuck with Turkey.

Anyway, regarding the fleet. I appreciate your explanation, and I understand your discomfort with Austria's rather unjustified stance. I can certainly engage Austria in accepting an unequal peace settlement, but let us settle some things first.

How exactly do you plan to employ your three fleets, if not to break through Ionian? What would you look after, and how could you possibly arrange them so that they're not a clear an constant threat to my most vital position?
3 ITALY -> TURKEY: Regarding Austria,Germany and Russia, (the message was sent incomplete due to some random choice process. For some reason I entered 'send' instead of enter. Anyway) I understand Russia might fall apart if England pushes in, but right now I'd say Germany is the one at pains. I mean, thanks to some inadequate orders last season, Russia can conceivably take Munich in the Spring. Who knows what may happen then?

But, more importantly, regarding Austria... While I get your frustration, and would likely behave just as you're doing, in trying to guarantee a favourable peace settlement, suited to the circumstances, I can also understand why Austria would be reluctant to accept one.

Not the terms. I'm complete agreement with you that anything agreed with Austria must take in account the positions you now command. But, even if I were to persuade Austria of that, how is Austria to trust you actually intend to move against Russia? As it stands, anyone with minimum knowledge of the rules would look at the board and assume you to be headed against Austria and against me.

Why, and how, would Austria believe otherwise?

If we can answer these questions, I'm more than eager to work towards ever-elusive peace in the Balkans!

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> FRANCE: Your move to W Med. Is that to try to attack Tunis? Or to move out to MAO? Would you want to bounce Tunis with me to keep me where I am? Or do you want to get out to MAO asap?
1 FRANCE -> ITALY: Hi Italy,

Thanks for keeping press up. I took a little break from this game given I didn't need to do anything the last couple of turns and I had other things on my plate. Your messages in the meanwhile are much appreciated.

I moved to Wes to keep all options open. To block if Austria would be coming from it, to allow moving for it before Turkey or Austria could take it, and to leave my options open in term of Mao.

You once told me your centers would be better in my hands than in Austria's, which I'd kindly agree with. Do you still think that is the case? If so, could we ensure I take Tun before Austria can take it. A/T seems heading to a strong alliance so they may be better off in my hands to help get builds to fight both of them.

I am not sure what you consider, but this could be a good idea more longterm.
2 ITALY -> FRANCE: You're asking quite a lot with that. You're asking me to give up and lose here and now.

Why not keep me around? If you take Tunis, you'd have to rebuild a unit and then deploy it into the Med for it to be effective here. Why not let me operate as a puppet state for you? A fleet already in the Ionian is something you can't get for years to come.

So while one of your units would be Green, it is still in a more advanced position than you'd be able to get for a while to come.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Hi Russia, sorry about not getting back to you sooner. I didn't have much time to devote to the game at the end of last week with work getting hectic. With the weekend here, I finally have some time to sit down and get to some proper diploming.

Thanks for the support hold on Bulgaria as Turkey certainly looked threatening with those three units around Bul. Interesting moves from him at the end of the day. Perhaps, he actually does intend to just let me have his centers, but likely he just figured I wouldn't try that risky move.

Italy wanted me to give him Greece last turn, but I "mis-ordered" Gre->Ion instead of Gre->Aeg to keep it from him. I think I've convinced him that it was an honest mistake, but waiving the build seems to have really sealed the ruse; and even without that build, I can still force Venice.

Tough break with England taking Sweden. That was certainly came down to guesswork. However, covering Norway and putting Germany into the North Sea was the better move, as you can just force back Sweden this turn.

I think we're in good shape moving forward. What are your thoughts?
1 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: Yeah, the Sweden thing was unfortunate but hopefully not a long term hiccup. I'm interested to see what Germany and France do this turn; I've heard that the move to Burgundy was prearranged but I doubt Germany will back off...doesn't seem like his style, really.

With regards to Italy, you have a great shot at Venice this year, hopefully he won't convoy to Apulia. I recommended that he go to Syria, which would be nice for you. As for Turkey, we'll see this year whether he is serious about letting you into his centers. I assume he'll bounce himself in Ankara and cover Con with Aeg but who knows. What are your plans with your one fleet?
2 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: I think I'll just use the fleet to cover Bul as Turkey is liable to try anything at this point.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: I think you made a wise choice and if you, italy, and I stick together we can make this game work very well for us. i want to be able to rely on you wholeheartedly, and I think letting italy help me with France will allow me a bigger hand in helping you against Russia. does that seem like the best way forward to you as well?
1 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: so we have some time left... lets try to finalize our plans here. are you ready to hit russia? if you are, you get rumania and put an army in gal this spring, in the fall, I'll be there to help.

i'm fine with you taking rum, sev and mos as well as the turkish centers you plan to split with italy while I get stp, war and nwy. I'd even be willing to give you warsaw in the medium term to even things out as that also gives us both a better stalemate position so we dont threaten each other. what do you think?
2 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I'm glad to hear your continued enthusiastic for the CPA. I really feel that it's the best course of action for us three to be successful in this game.

Yes, I think it would be a good time to move on Russia. I won't ask for the specifics of the maneuvers, but I hope to see your troops rolling in at Russia in the mid-term.

Long term, regarding the division of lands, all of that sounds quite reasonable. We can sort out the details once we get there and have a clearer view of the situation. Of course, ensuring an equitable and defensible position for both is the primary goal.

How are things going in the west? Are relations with France getting better since the foray into Burgundy?
3 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: let me say this... France and I are talking through things constructively... but i want to tell you a secret. I only tell you this because you and I have committed to this CPA triangle and to show you that I trust you. France has told me you asked him about my move, and he asked me permission to tell you that he's pissed at me. so he will tell you we are at war, and my answer to you will be we are at 'war'. we are working out a deal to make it look like we continue to remain at war while nothing changes hands... I tell you this in the strictest of confidence and please please do not share this intel with russia or italy.

you can tell them I've said 'we are discussing paths to peace but there is little trust' or something like that... but what is important is that France also wants me to attack Russia and working out a deal with France will be relatively important in moving on Russia.

if you manage to take rumania and take gal in the spring, I will do my part in the north.
4 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Thanks for keeping me the loop about that. I have and will certainly keep that in the strictest confidence. By the way, all I asked France was what he thought about it. I hadn't spoke with him in a while, and felt like opening by asking about the elephant in the room.

I got an interesting piece of press from Russia. He said he thought the move into Burgundy may have been prearranged. I didn't ask about that with him, he just brought that up as a random remark during conversation.

0 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: What the hell was Bla doing trying to move to Con??

That aside, it was a pretty successful turn!

Hope your interview went well. Attempted stab aside, please can Bla attack Bulgaria? Then I can make it through this move. The Germans are coming....

And by the way, after your last move there is no damn way I am going to move Ank > Smy, so don't be tempted. Ank S Syr > Smy, Con S Bla > Bul.
1 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Bla > Bul is really quite likely to work, as well.
2 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: That was a misorder/misread. Clearly Black sea couldn't do anything by way of support, and I thought you had asked for it (somehow I misread "Bla supported Con's hold." as "Bla move to Con"). This was rational because Italy was always going to play a unit to Con, I thought. My mistake- I should have been more careful- and I don't ask you to believe me here, I know it must sound like bull.
3 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: btw, I'm thinking perhaps Bla-rum is stronger than Bla-bul?
4 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Erm, for whom???? Bla-rum is me out of the game!!

I certainly hope that's not the order you've entered. It doesn't achieve anything for either of us. I am in big danger of Bul S Aeg > Con! Bla > Bul is the ONLY thing that stops this. I can't be sure what Aeg is doing. PLEASE just move to Bul and take the support offered in there. If he repeats last turn's moves, you gain Bul. How could that be bad??

Hoping you read this in time.....
5 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Constantinople is supporting Black Sea to Bulgaria. Please do not
a) Misorder
b) Get confused
c) Forget
d) Doubt
..... I really really need you not to let me down here. Don't make me beg.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: Ready to talk again? With your build this year, you should have good security against an Austrian stab, if you so stab. As for me, I don't mind stabs as much as I get annoyed by allies that miss key turns. ~N~ ~N~ I still need to see Germany out of this one, and the less help you give him, the better. I understand your concerns with my units in the north. I've been trying to figure out how we can keep ourselves safe without inflating the units. Would the following work: ~N~ ~N~ St. Pete back to Moscow, Finland to St. Pete, Gulf of Bothnia holds. ~N~ ~N~ Sweden holds, Norway holds. Kiel takes Berlin (or perhaps we work it out so you get Berlin), I move the rest of my fleets back. We can then bounce in Finland if we feel the need. ~N~ ~N~ The problem I see is that if you remained allied with Austria, that is a bigger problem for me that my alliance with France is for you. France doesn't really factor in it for you, since you by association have Italy on your side with no southern threat. If you build Warsaw, you can move that back to Moscow easily, or to Purssia, while Austria moves to Boh. It's a tough position for me. ~N~ ~N~ Of course, Austria could still be fake stabbing, like he pretended he would years ago. Who am I to tell? ~N~ ~N~ Thoughts?
1 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: OK, two things. Firstly, I stand by my need to maintain Germany in Berlin. I don't think you eliminating Germany as a power is as important to you as the opportunity of providing a land outlet to Russia. I am skeptical. ~N~ ~N~ Secondly, I am in favor of demilitarization of Scandinavia; however, not to your prescription, which includes me retreating and you holding. Let's continue talking on that. If we are to demilitarize Scand, those units must go somewhere... ~N~ ~N~ So, here's a thought we might want to begin kicking around... You really want me to stab Austria, eh? Well, I think you should stab France. Would you be interested in a complete double shift? North vs. South? I think we would have an advantage, especially if Italy continues its anti-FRENCH moves.
2 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: I am interested, but the problem is if you maintain Germany, and Italy is still fighting, France falls quickly while you and Austria potentially gain crucial ground. Ideally we both shift at the same time, but it is very dangerous for me to stab my only ally when you have three. Hence why I need Germany out of this, one way or the other.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: it might be a stretch, but what do you think about moving piardy to the channel in autumn ?

a simple move, but it will entirely disrupt any hopes england is having on defence. for you to get london, we will have to get one of your armies unto the island, and for that we will have to get enough fleet-leverage

since the little accident in brest allowed england to keep his fleet in western med, I guess your fleet in spain will be stuck defending for the time being - we will have to work together to break englands defencess. as long as he can support hold in the north sea. I don't have enough fleets, neither do you, but together, taking england out will be easy

what we have to lock out for is whatever he is planning in the south with his fleet. as your southcoast is rather timidly defenced, he can cause too much mishief. imagine him grabbing portugal - it would take ages to get him out of there

so here is what I would suggest

in spring, you retake brest with paris. to defend yourself from possible mishief, burgundy should cover gascony. that way it can support brest, and still defend marsailles or even spain, should the need arise

meanwhile, spain you should think about sending spain to MAO. there are some risks involved with that darned fleet in the south, so I will leave the decision to you on that. but eventually it will be useful when taking on liverpool, and faster than building another fleet in marsailles and slowly moving it around to get england

then in spring, you should hit the english channel, so that we can break the north-sea, and with that, all what is left of england that he could have used to defend himself

from there, we will have to take the channel the following turn, and then start gathering what is left of england.



alternatively, which is also a fun option to explore, is already hitting the channel in spring - disconnecting his fleets.



at any rate, those are just suggestions, and I would like to hear what you think would be the best option, so that we coordinate accordingly.

since the timezones are somewhat in the way, I don't know wether you will be still awake, or already awake, or something inbetween by the time the moves change, but for me it will be around 12 am, so chances are we won#t have much time for discussion - meaning whatever you decide for now is probably the final word in the matter



lastly, a minor issue about the fairness of our deal. with england split london/liverpool to you, edi to me, we end on a 7/9. I think that could go fairer.
so I am willing to renegotiate belgium, which you probably still hold against me anyway, removing unnecessary reasons for anyone of us being dissatisfied.

while I can clearly say that I refuse to hand over belgium immediatly this very turn, as it only exposes both of us to unnecessary risks (not to mention that our attention should lay on england. if we give him too much time to breath, it will only mean more work for us).

I am however willing to return belgium to you, as soon as I get one of my fleets into the north sea - with your help.

once I am there, there is no risk for either of us involved in switching belgium to you.

I would like to hear what you think about this matter
1 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I hear tell that it's [1517907] to look a gift horse in the mouth. I'll take whatever scraps you'll feed me, Belgium included.

The way I see it, England can be certain of defending Brest only by keeping both fleets where they are. Which is a waste, I think, because I can easily defend Spain, Portugal and Marseilles from one fleet. I'll head to the Channel and to Brest, I'm pretty sure I'll end up taking one of them.

We have three hours for discussion. I'll be watching this space till then.

Oh, and sorry for not writing for so long.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: By the way, England didn't offer me anything. He just told me you were a [147642]. Whatever that is.
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: it's not scraps

it's fair
4 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Yeah, yeah, I know. I make joke, you see?

Anyway, if you feed me enough scraps to make a meal, then it's more than fair. I have no right to one after such losses.

Would you like a more polite answer? I shall happily accept Belgium from you, your honourable [300351].
5 GERMANY -> FRANCE: haha.

at any rate, let's clean up england quickly and neatly. the sooner we can force him to disband his units behind our lines, the less trouble we will have

0 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Hi England, still too bad you were unable to take my support in Edi, as you could have been at two again. Perhaps you did not trust me anymore? I'd understand that.

The superpower in this game will likely be Turkey, with A/R at war, and both of them pushed back rather significantly already by Turkey. This turn may therefore be important to decide whether you'd prefer to help me against Germany, or whether you help Germany. Germany is clearly set to attack Russia and I'd be happy to avoid that to ensure that Russia has sufficient strength to fight the southeast.

What do you think?
1 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Sorry, with a lack of communication, I don't really have time, but I will write you back today for sure.
2 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: No, I trust you, but as I wrote I will try to maintain a balanced power between you and Germany. Even if I lose territory in this. I'm not sure about that this is good strategy. I agree that Turkey is in a very good situation, but it is very similar for you. You both don't really have enemies who attacking you and have possibilities to grow, but everybody should be careful if Germany turns fully against you, it is still a good possibilty for Turkey to go through Russia. And then you need to try to help Germany.
But I can understand that you want to move against Germany. I can't see now who can be the 3rd in a draw. And this way Turkey for sure has chance to be the leader.
What shall I do if I would help you?
3 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Allowing Russia to fight Turkey means attacking Germany. That way he will come at me immediately, that much is clear, but it can help. A move to Nth now to take Hol or Edi could be an idea although I am not sure I should have disclosed this.
4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Considering that I am unsure which way you will lean
5 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Happy to discuss

0 GERMANY -> ITALY: Yes indeed! Can we keep Gas dmz? In return i will supp you to brest if you get into mao
1 ITALY -> GERMANY: I assume you meant Burgundy? I mean, it seems that our strongest moveset is precisely Spain moving to Gascony, so that we can ensure we triumph against Brest in the Autumn.

More specifically, if we order Por-mao, Spa-gas and Par S Spa-gas, England can bounce Por-mao, but can't stop Spa-gas. In the Autumn, England will be forced to choose between support holding Brest or bouncing Por-mao. Even if England decides to defend Brest, this means Por-mao succeeds and we're absolutely certain to get Brest next Spring.

What do you say? Burgundy, as far as I'm concerned, is definitely to be a DMZ!
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: Meanwhile, I'll see if I can get the new fleet to move West, so that England can't hope to retaliate against you.

The issue regarding the East is a bit more complicated, though. I can stall Turkey in the Sea, but how can we best support Austria? Even if Austria can't be propped up indefinitely, we should delay its collapse as much as possible. Do you think we risk Trieste falling and order Ven-tyr? If Trieste makes it, our position is surely stronger to push Russia back.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: Ok spain to gas. I guess you need me to hold back the russians & turks, so i am a better ally for you than the brits.
4 ITALY -> GERMANY: To be perfectly honest, I think you're an ally without which I can't hope to stay in one piece. I've being doing my best to prop Austria, as I can't hope to withstand them without Austria. If, or rather, when, Austria is further weakened, I can't possibly hope to hold my own against Russia and Turkey by my own (nor, as a matter of fact, can you). To make things worse, Russia does not answer me at all, meaning I can't possibly drive a wedge between them. If one of us goes under the bus, so does the other.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I don't think I can stress how important maintaining parity is for me. It's something that's tremendously worrying. I understand your concerns regarding a balance in the East, but I'd really appreciate an overall balance, since an imbalance in the East can be corrected later on much more easily. Is that all right?

My moves this turn were completely stifled. With F Albania, though, I think we can make our devastating attack this turn. I think an attack involving you supporting me into Vienna from Tyrolia, into Serbia from Bulgaria, and into Trieste from Vienna would work. That's, of course, assuming we're both okay with SC parity. What do you think?
1 RUSSIA -> ITALY: How's this: I support you into Vienna, you take Trieste, and you hit Serbia while I take Budapest, then you take Serbia next year?
2 ITALY -> RUSSIA: That would be superb. You're not covering Warsaw, though?

I'm a bit unclear, though, are you okay with the parity thing? My maximal apologies for bringing it up yet again, but I'm still not clear as to what the resolution of the issue was, and I'd like for us to be in agreement!
3 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I'll be covering Warsaw with Silesia.
4 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I'm fine with trying to keep a relative balance in Scs, but I hope you understand my concern with all of your Scs and units being in the East while a third of my units are out in the Atlantic.
5 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I completely understand. We discussed briefly our plans for withdrawing forces after we take Austria, which is something we can hash out further and implement. After Austria, I'd like to shift my focus to the west and take out France and Germany quickly for our draw with England.

2 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Hey there.

Depending on how much Turkey trusts me, I think the best option may be for him to move the first fleet through tun into wes in the fall, but to follow it with the other fleet moving into ion in the spring and then tun in the fall. For some reason, the Italians aren't too fond of me, but if you can convince them to mess with France for a while, I would not complain.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Just realised there is only 7 hrs left on the clock.

I think your moves read fine. I will be ordering: Bul supports Gal to Rum. Aegean holds Bul, Ionian to East Med, Nap to Ionian, Apu holds.
1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: PS - one thing to throw into the mix - Turkey has just offered me support from Bul to Rum because he 'wants to get one over on Russia...'
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Do you think you can trust him? And how much time do you have to discuss moves?

If he can be trusted, then Bul>Rum and Tun>Bul could work, Galicia could go for Ukraine and we might be able to [344508] up Sevastopol this year as well.

Then again, from what I've heard of PB, giving up and petulantly lashing out at someone for betraying him doesn't really seem in character.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Hmm, actually, we were to try Bul>Rum Turkey/Russia could counter it with Rum>Bul supported by Con and Bla.

Or, to similar effect they could do:
Sil>Gal
Sev sup hold Rum
Rum sup Bla/Con>Bul
Bla/Con>Bul
Bla/Con sup Bla/Con>Bul
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: "Do you think you can trust him? And how much time do you have to discuss moves?"

No, and none, so that sorts that out.

Let's stick with the original plan - checking over your moves, it's too risky to try and keep Turkey in the loop, especially when I'm going to be taking another centre off him this year.
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Sounds good.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> ITALY: France is proposing three way draw with you - I am checking if you have the same information...
1 ITALY -> ENGLAND: Indeed, I'm up for it if you are. He sent me this message, did he send the same one to you?

CC: Italy, England

We have some time, but I think the following moves make sense and welcome any feedback:

Italy: PIE > TYR; TUS > VEN; GOL > TYR; WES > TUN
France: NAF > WES; BUR > MUN; MAR > BUR; GAS > PAR; IRI > MAO
England: ENG > BEL; LIV > WAL; NTH S ENG > BEL; NOR H; STP H
2 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Yes, I got the same message. And I agree we join our forces and go for three way draw. Otherwise we are dead on the long run. So I am in.
3 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Here is my answer and France agreed with slight changes...

So I have checked Italy and you have bought us both. About moves, I have second thoughts. Escape route from BEL is PIC, so you need to be able to defend Brest. Further on we will not be able to keep BEL (possible situation is G army in PIC, RUH, fleet in HOL and DEN could cut NTH).

My idea (Italy's moves stay the same):
England: NTH>SKA, EC>NTH, LIV>WAL, NOR S NTH>SKA (attacking SWE or DEN,), STP S MOS
France: IRI>EC (to attack BEL), NAF>MAO (defending BRE), GAS>PAR, BUR>MUN, MAR>BUR
4 ITALY -> ENGLAND: One reason France proposed different moves to those was to get more fleets in the Mediterranean, so I'm cautious about keeping both his fleets up north. You could cover Brest using France's Irish Sea fleet (once it's moved to EC), meaning the North Africa fleet could stay in the Med?

Regarding the other changes I'll leave that to you two as it concerns the northern theatre. However I do agree that Bel will be harder to defend in the short term until France's army moves through Paris to Pic. I like the idea of moving to Ska to worry Swe, but you simply must make sure that the North Sea is yours, otherwise we're in big trouble.

intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: well done on the [74197] of greece. ~N~ Where do we go from here? ~N~ ~N~ I was thinking a combination of R/T/F vs G/I ~N~ ~N~ Our DMZ is working fairly well, and I think it should stay in place. We need to discuss the Vie/Tri/Alb problem. I can always offer support, from Budapest if it is needed. ~N~ K
1 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Sounds good - G/I is in the way of both of us, but France isn't in a position to attack Italy right now (and doesn't look to be going after Germany either, unless he suddenly moves Belgium to Holland, Picardy to Belgium, Burgandy to Ruhr, and Marseilles to Burgandy and gets you to hit Berlin to break support of Munich for him). Suggesting to France that he could pick up two centers this turn might get him to bite, and F Mar built at the end of the year would help against Italy. ~N~ ~N~ I think Italy will hold both Trieste and Vienna this turn, so if you support Serbia into Trieste, I'm sure Venice will be holding it so Italy will keep it - is there any way you can move around to occupy Bohemia, Galicia, and Budapest? This would put you in a good position to take Vienna if I hit Trieste with Serbia. I am considering moving Greece to Albania, and Aegean to Greece, forcing Albania to retreat to Adriatic. I'm also considering moving Smyrna out to Eastern Med and hopefully getting into Ionian soon. Not sure if it's worth risking losing Greece and getting it back again next turn, though, since Italy might anticipate and use Ionian to bounce me out of Eastern Med.
2 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: France has been hectoring me since the begining of this game to attack germany, now that I have made the first moves I am pretty sure that he'll jump on the chance to prosper from the fall of germany. I will suggest to him however that he also considers moving A Bur - Ruh to place pressure on Munich. ~N~ ~N~ I to am pretty sure Italy will place support on both Vie & Tri this season. I was already considering moving a Gal - Sil, but am thinking seriously about amending this to Gal - Boh. regarding Serbia I would be grateful if you would consider supporting my army budapest - hold. this is just in case Germany's A Vie decides to support A Tri - Bud.
3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: I can hold Budapest. I think you're probably right, although I also wouldn't be surprised if Trieste hits Serbia in order to break support of Greece. But Aegean will support Greece, so Serbia will be free to support the hold.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: France,

It is always difficult during a game of diplomacy to tell the difference between truth and lies. And yet here I am. Are you truly telling me that no more German bases will be under attack? Yet the more I listen to some of the others, the more the truth becomes more convoluted and difficult to determine.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: I've clearly made a mistake. Several of them in a row. I've allowed this game to not devoted to press necessary to maintain the position. The calm was broken and the tide has turned against me. I ask myself. Where Shall I go? I would like to create more trust between us. so that the demise of Russia need not be seen as the end times, a point of tremendous contention, but rather the point of alliance through difficulties.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Hi Germany,

I was not telling you that I will stop attacking you. Quite the contrary, I was saying that I will probably need to continue the attack I started earlier, unless you saw a good reason for me not to do so.

All I wanted to explain, was what got me to attack you and that it was a number of factors all together.

Now, I did see your retreat to Den and that actually gives me hope. I think we may be able to solve this and put both you and me in an excellent position still.

Kind regards,
France
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: France,
Yes, but how many bases Am I likely to lose? should I find myself in a hopeless position, I would be very discouraged. I have given signs of good faith Towards you. What more are you looking for.
Germany
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Will we even the scales of this alliance after this turn? Where we both have an even number of bases. Honestly, After Ive shown good faith? Or are you going to continue to attack me?
5 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Hi Germany,

I am not really saying you haven't given signs of good faith to me last turn. I am saying more that, due to earlier actions and due to how the map has played out, I saw no other option than to attack and indeed continue to attack.

On the number of bases, let me turn the question around. How many bases would you like to have after this turn?

Are you okay with me taking England while you take the entire of Scandinavia? And what about Hol?

You will likely get two Russian bases (Nwy and War) if you play it well. That would bring you to 7 even if you would lose Edi and Hol. Is that sufficient or not?

Perhaps we can find a solution still, although we have only three hours to go.

Kind regards,
France

1 ITALY -> FRANCE: Actually, if you are interested in stopping the Eastern march of the Russia and Turkey it's in a good place. I know you are strongly allied with Russia--who in turn is strongly allied with Turkey. If I really thought that I had a place in a four-way draw with you guys, I might not worry as much. As I always say: When in doubt, do what's going to piss Germany off the most ;) That is, get on Russia's good side as much as possible and convince him to work with you rather than Turkey. Turkey's not in a great position either, I'm not so sure Russia wouldn't consider a stab. I do think you still have a shot, but it's going to take some good tactics and some luck.

Regardless, I bet you'll hold the Ionian for a while at least, I'm moving Marseilles back into Spain.
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: Thanks! There may be some openings in the East. I am in touch with Russia and have told him I am open to almost any cooperative option. I desperately need to get a build, however, to stay relevant in this game. I appreciate having the fleet retreated. Good luck!

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: England has been telling me you're preparing an attack, I can see now that this was all a lie, he has been secretly planning an invasion with Russia and Italy. Fortunately, Austria is wise. I'll move Burgundy out.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: I don't know why you've turned so against me, I have never taken any aggressive actions against you (Burgundy doesn't even count, as I told you when, where and why- to get rid of our common enemy England, and I promptly moved back out.) Really, are you planning on allying with England? Even as he's moving toward Port/Spain ? The guy who breaks every alliance as soon as there's the first chance to stab?
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I don't trust either of you too much; you did not leave Burgundy when requested, and in fact support-held there. You did leave this turn, but still- it was long overdue, and I can't be sure it was because you were holding up your end of the deal, or due to pressures elsewhere. ~N~ ~N~ Don't think I haven't noticed England, too. I can't be too sure of anyone, so I'm always open to ideas, and hostile to either of you- but neither am I an ally to be used to destroy you or England. ~N~ ~N~ I honestly don't know what on earth you and England are doing, especially considering the state of the Austrian-turkish power grab. But since a western triangle alliance is a folly, especially now since it seems we all either distrust or openly fight each other, I will listen to you both, and my other allies, and destermine what is best for myself- and for the West's protection against that Austrian-turkish alliance.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: thank you once again for the detailed message. I will respond to it later tonight. I have some ideas to run by you as well.
1 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: It's a shame that we have to do this at the last minute again.
2 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: I am sorry it is getting to it again... my life is far too busy and I have so little time to devote to these games... but thankfully over 11 hours still remain.

thank you for your message, but I do think your initial point about not trusting me might be more accurate. I am not about to concede North, and I will be honest with you once again that I'm considering convoys to Norrway, York or Edi from Bel. I'm not sure which route I will take. most likely you will have to play somewhat defensively to protect against me, and that is what I expect.

I do not have a desire to eliminate you out of 'spite' or any such thing... but I do intend to make sure you are limited to no more than 4 or 5 units max. I have a sense I'm going to be stabbed by Austria or Italy or both in the near future and at that time, either you will help them eliminate me, in which case Austria gets a beautiful solo shot, or I will help you survive so we end in a 4 or potentially 5 way draw.

As for the suggestion I initially wanted to offer. if you choose to go back to the role of subservient power without demanding North or even a dmz at this point (that offer was honest last year, but no longer useful now), then there is a path for us to work together and for you to survive long enough to vie for a spot in the draw.

that is to move into the Med. forgo por which will likely bounce anyways, and instead go for Naf and move NAO to MAO. you keep your home centers/units + stp for 4... you disband stp and push south. if you really wanted to do well, you'd even move Lon to Ech and get ready to take bre. if you actually move in that direction, then I can promise you aid into brest and to leave your home centers alone. but otherwise, I'm going to try to figure out a way to cut you out of the picture as quickly as I can so I can turn around to face italy/austria.

i'm sorry if my honesty is not welcomed at this point, but I don't see a reason to lie to you.
3 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: What I'm really hearing is that you have some sort of Central Triple going on as I once suggested you might, but that you're hoping I'll help you solo somehow.

Meh! If it means my survival, that's something I can deal with. It would be wonderful though if you resisted the urge to invade more of my lands than you really need to.
4 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: you are very good.

yes. what I'm saying is by pretending to help me solo, you have the best shot at getting a spot in the draw. i can resist taking MUCH more of your land, and I can steer clear of your island. but i'm going to take your northern holdings.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: What I have just sent to Russia and France:

Austria and I are talking frantically with France to try and get him to stop assisting Germany to the win.

That, frankly, was the outcome I hadn't expected. I had expected F and G to be fighting, whilst, honestly, Austria and I eventually removed you two, leading to a joint alliance against one of the two bigger powers, leading to a 3 way draw with A/I and one of F and G.,

The stab by Germany, yet with France assisting, has left me gobsmacked - I never expected that, especially as, in league play, he gets no points for a second place to a win.

Austria and I now have no choice - we have to work with everyone left - you, me and him, to try and achieve a draw. France will, I think, work with us as he has said he will switch sides as long as he can guarantee particpating in a draw that leaves him surviving.

I think a blockade is workable here. Moscow and Sev support each other, Ukraine supports Warsaw, Gal supports Warsaw, Rum supports Gal, Vienna and Tyrolia support each other, Venice works with Rome, whilst Adriatic, Ionian, Mars, MAO, Tunis fleets can set up a blockade in the west.

Smyrna, Sev and Bul can take down the remains of Turkey, leading to an extra unit for Italy and Russia to assist in stalemate duties.

France, Austria, Russia and Italy work for a five way draw with Germany - eminently achievable, as the stalemate line is already there in most places.

I'm copying this to all parties - France, Austria and Russia (to who this message was originally written).

I seriously think this will work. Otherwise, we just limply hand the win to Germany, and concede defeat in the League season after just two games, as a win in the last two games is unlikely...
1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Trying to persuade France, but it's not looking good. I'll paste you my chat to him if you want?
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Sure, sounds good.

The insanity of France's moves make me wonder if it's not actually an inter-game agreement (he'll throw this one for [432255], and then [432255] will do likewise in a later game). Otherwise, it just makes no sense.
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I realise this - here's his press to me, then mine to him:

I admire your persistence and the attention you have given this plan. There are several problems, however, the foremost being the size of this operation. You want a grand alliance, and while it is a goal to remain in the game and have a chance at a draw, getting five players to hold together is difficult, especially when splitting between fewer players yields more points. At six centres, Austria is not so far behind that a split with Germany wouldn't be a bad thing. That is one thought.

For my personal position, Germany can would not have to do much to dispose of me. Yes, you and Austria can send your forces to assist me, but then we have a long game of defense against the German fleet, which has no one to attack but me, and I be down to just the Iberian. That this is my own fault is not lost on me, but I was trying a novel tactic which did not work.

Ultimately, and this is really my driving criteria in evaluating this, is that a five way draw is not as helpful in the long term for the league. It is not lost in the second game, as you said. [432255] is a new player, so a solo is 12 points total for him. [1038194], PB, and I think [1134393] took 3 points each last game. A five way split gives us each 2.4 points, or something like that, upping their total. Motivation wise, it make the next few games more appealing for them to group together to try for the top three spots, together, with tight competition for the forth. It's just logical, since it serves their mutual benefit. Not that I am accusing them of playing that way, but it's something I consider. I am not just letting Germany win, but I am not in the right position to strike, and I am detest playing a purely defensive game for the sake of a five way draw. If it is down to three or four of us, then that makes more sense to me.

I appreciate your efforts in trying to orchestrate the alliance, and I don't mean to be rude, since I hate to see my own plans fall through. But for the moment, I am not going to go along with it. I tell you that up front, rather than lead you on.
03:58 PM Oh balls - that didn't send!

I sent you a very long email message and it didn't send - I'll type again, as it's worth sending.
04:55 PM Right, that didn't send properly, so here goes.

Firstly, the size isn't an issue. We are already on the stalemate line all along the eastern front down to Switzerland. The only place it is not in place is around Spain and West Med. With your fleets in Tunis, in MAO, Mars, and our fleets in Ionian/Adr, it will be easy to set up a stalemate line that will last.

If it's a long defence, so what? Key here is not to let Germany win. You say that you will benefit from letting [432255] win. This is just wrong!! Let me lay out the two tables & firstly if [432255] wins, then if we obtain a draw:

[432255] wins:

[432255] 12
TGM 4
[1038194] 4
[1052172] Bear 4
[244023] 0
[651562] 0
[1134393] 0


And if it's a draw:

TGM 6.4
[1038194] 4
[1052172] Bear 4
[432255] 2.4
[244023] 2.4
[156027] 2.4
[1134393] 2.4


In other words, if you go for the draw, you are only 4 points behind the leader, and 1.6 points behind second place. If you let Germany win, you will be 12 points behind the leader, and 4 points behind second place, on equal 4th.

Clearly, it makes sense to go for the draw, especially as 2 of the players who drew in the first game & [1038194] and [1052172] bear, will be knocked out in game 2 before a possible draw.

Yes, a five way draw isn't pretty, but it's in your and our best interests here. You can't win, so go for the draw.

Here are 5 good reasons for changing your mind:

1. Doing the stalemate line in the west is easy & we have the fleets to do it
2. Doing the stalemate line in the east is easy & it's there already
3. Germany will have a long stalemate line to defend.
4. Germany can get to 16 units (with the 3 English centres) but no further & guaranteed draw.
5. If you go for the draw, it will ensure you get points, rise up the league table, and improve your personal statistics with a draw, not a defeat.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Am moving to Venice from ADR - if you can support, that would help. France isn't going to help.
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: I could, but then if we forced him out he could retreat to Trieste.

0 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Hello again. Clearly the Russian will not go down without a fight. Could we agree to not attack each other's territories and instead co-operate against the Russian?
1 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I agree not to attack you or move onto your territory. I also volunteer to get out of Tyrolia as soon as I can make Italy either submit to a Ionian DMZ or I own Venice. I'm sure you won't mind either of those results.

As for moving on Russia, I cannot do that yet because that would be my death. He and Italy would tag-team me into oblivion. Currently Russia thinks I'm an honest bloke, and I don't want to waste that sentiment just yet.

I think it would be beneficial if you focus on Russia while I focus on Italy. However, if Turkey helps me against an Italian attack, I would gladly reciprocate him. He doesn't trust me for obvious reasons, but a word from you may help him not be persuaded by Italy. A strong Turkey is in your best interest against Russia, and I'm willing to defend and support Turkey.
2 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Thank you. As usual, it's great to work with you. I will naturally have to focus on Russia, and I appreciate your non-aggression in the south. Good luck with your campaigns, and when you can vacate Tyrolia, know that I will respect that demilitarized zone. Thank you for your cooperation and good-natured diplomacy.

Regards,
Germany

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: Look, here's how the situation looks to me in Germany: You have Munich, but you likely won't be able to hold it, as Austria will probably try for it, and later France, and meanwhile you've got Austria dangerously close to Warsaw. Berlin you could probably take back, with help from England. But the point is, after I'm defeated you're going to be facing the English/French alliance to the West, and Austria/Turkey to the South, and you without allies fighting on two fronts.
1 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: (Italy isn't much help to you right now)
2 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: So here's what I'm proposing: Since we're both interested in gaining SC while making sure England doesn't get stronger: Allow me to keep Berlin, and I will support Baltic Sea to Denmark, from there you can take Sweden and Norway, I will use my two fleets to fight England at Helgoland and NTH Sea. You gain three SC for one, England is much weakened, France is held at bay and you will have a loyal Ally in Germany to work with.
3 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: The Alternative is, I assist Austria in taking Munich, fight you at Berlin, and you make no forward gains until England comes knocking at your door.
4 GERMANY -> GERMANY: France ([148279]) is the biggest BULLSHITTER, he has been allied with England this whole time, and been lying to me about it, claiming he's not 'actively' aligned with anyone. England ([1145339]) is worse
5 GERMANY -> GERMANY: I would tell France directly to his face, but don't want to anger him in future league games, but I'll take note!
6 GERMANY -> GERMANY: I think my big mistake was not allying fully and quickly with one of Russia, England or France. I tried to ally with France and play neutral between England and Russia in Sweden, but France was slow to ally and England 'allied' late and only in pretense as he prepared the stab. Russia quickly moved in for the kill. :(
7 GERMANY -> GERMANY: It wasn't until late Autumn 1902 that England agreed to ally, I need to ally quicker.
8 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: You make a compelling offer. I am uncertain at present.

0 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: 12 more hours and you'll get some good thoughts from me. I'd like for us to agree to a set of moves this season so we can both see that we are indeed interested in working together long-term, so think on that a bit for now and feel free to propose some moves for this season to get the ball rolling, I'll propose some moves myself within those 12 hours.

It is pretty clear to me that you and the Turk are aligned, so unless you work with me against Turkey, or move against Turkey in some what, I will assume you are still against me. I think actions will speak louder than words, though I am open to ideas you may have for this season and beyond, so let me know if you have any thoughts on that front.
3 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Hmmm, you are MUCH too quiet. You have failed another test of mine, though this time I have the time to follow up on the situation before it's too late! ;-)

In case you haven't noticed, the F/G is well on it's way, England only has two units and will be surrounded and dead very quickly. My personal opinion is the the F/G is the most powerful alliance this game has to offer, especially since it isn't as obvious as the R/T. Anyway, the longer there is chaos in the southeast, the higher the chances of the F/G taking over this game and killing all of us in the southeast, you agree with that don't you?!

My earlier statements about an Eastern Triple were 100% sincere, especially in a WTA 14,000 pot game! We need to kill off the Turk and get ready to defend against the German ASAP while Italy stalemates the Frenchman in the Med before it's too late and we all lose our 2,000 points and Ghost-rating, in my opinion.

The move to Gal was defensive when you refused to communicate earlier, but here's what I propose. Aeg hits Con to allow Italy to take Smy and build a fleet to slow down the Frenchman. Serb attacks Bul with support from Rum while Bud supports hold at Gal to see if you will work with me. If you do work with me, I will vacate Gal next season. How does that sound?

I'd ask Sev to attack Black Sea to increase the odds of me getting Bul, but I'm sure that would freak you out and send red flags for an attack on Rum. That said, I think you can convince the Turk to have Black Sea support hold at Rum (or have Black Sea support hold at Bul while Bul supports hold at Rum, though in this case Sev would be needed to hit Black Sea for me to get Bul, which I understand may be too risky for you and you'd prefer to merely see me follow through with what I say I will do first... but I trust your judgement and ability to take advantage of the Turk if you want to do so).

Anyway, to summarize. I'm really hoping we can get an Eastern Triple going. The Italian is already getting pushy about getting Greece, supposedly so he can defend against the Frenchman, but with how buddy-buddy those two's moves were last season, I have a sneaking suspicion he may have cut a deal with France and may join the F/G in a Western Triple, which is an even bigger argument for the two of us to stick together. Oops, I digressed a bit there! ANYWAY, to be clear, and to follow up on another earlier point I made and was sincere about, I'd like the two of us to agree on moves this season so we can both see we are interested in working together and surviving this game. In that spirit, here are my orders:

Bud support hold at Gal. Serb to Bul, Alb to Gre and Aeg to Con.

Again, if/when you can help get me into Bul, I will vacate Galicia and hope you will join me in advancing on the German to slow down the F/G. I will also need to defend from a possible Italian stab as his units are sort of surrounding me and he will get a build that may very well be used against me while he maintains peace with France. My hope is that a little communication (or a lot!) is all the two of us need to have a game-long alliance with the goal being surviving this huge pot game. Are you with me?! :-)

0 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Well, you leave me with little choice in keeping defense in the north. If I leave Liv or Mos, that presents an opportunity for you to slip in. But! If we now follow our agreement of trading St. Pete for Swe, we can start semi-demilitarizing the area, meaning that I don't think either of us will completely trust the other immediately, but we can move Livonia and Barents out to more useful endeavors. What do you think?
1 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: That depends on where Warsaw is going.
2 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Warsaw was going to help defend Germany, which I think was pretty obvious and nothing I can easily cover up, especially if I moved to Silesia this turn. Does this affect your ability to trade Scs? ~N~ ~N~ I hope you don't plan on convoying to Norway. Really, [1084968], packing Scand full of armies won't help since ultimately St. Pete is a roadblock. I would recommend convoying to Hol since you lack armies on the mainland. I think we are in similar positions: we're afraid of the other getting builds and using those builds against one another. Because at this moment we're mostly even in the north, though you have the upper hand. ~N~ ~N~ So, what do you want to happen?
3 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: The problem is your support of Germany. If you help his holds, you are taking away my area to expand. If you want me to stab France, I need to finish Germany first, and take away the chance of him recovering. ~N~ ~N~ As for armies in the north, they like hanging out there, especially when Norway is so open.
4 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Norway isn't in danger. I have one unit, with which I have no hope of keeping Sweden and Norway. ~N~ ~N~ In order for me to not defend Germany, I need some sort of assurance or indication that you plan on stabbing France after destroying Germany. Right now it definitely seems more like you're preparing to attack me next, so I want to maintain Germany as a buffer. Convoying to Norway would only continue the indications that you plan on attacking me next and thus I need to defend Germany. If you want me to back off or even help take down Germany, show me that it will benefit me.
5 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: I could also go south towards Austria rather than move on you. It still comes down to trust, and while you certainly have more to lose with me in the north, I have more to lose by stabbing France while you are allied with Austria.

If we do this for a couple years, then turn back around on England, I think that would be a pretty great deal. But if it gets so bad that I have to start disbanding fleets, you're going to lose out on your opportunity to strike at England.
